title: pizza bread
directions: Thaw bread dough.
When thawed, roll on floured board until rectangular in shape.
Add pepperoni and shredded Mozzarella cheese, leaving about 1 inch of dough on edges with no cheese. Roll up dough, jelly roll fashion, and place, seam side down, in a ring on greased cookie sheet.
Bake according to bread recipe, or until brown on top.
Great!

title: spinach or broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place into greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli nut salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss with rest of ingredients and refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: louisiana yam pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into pastry shell and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
May be served with Cool Whip on top.

title: mom's coconut cake
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar gradually, creaming until light.
Add egg and vanilla and beat until fluffy.

title: jalapeno corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan. Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour half of this batter into pan. Cover evenly with half the cheese, then peppers, then remaining cheese. Top with remaining batter. Bake 1 hour.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: brian's raspberry-chocolate pie
directions: Roll puff pastry sheet (with flour) to fit inside 13 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes or until light brown. Cook pudding and milk according to pie recipe on pudding box. Stir in cream cheese on low heat and add powdered sugar.
Pour into prepared puff pastry.
Cool and top with raspberries and whipped cream, if desired.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat melt 1/4 cup spread. Add chicken and garlic powder.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 4 minutes.
Stir in remaining spread, mushrooms and peas; cook 2 minutes or until chicken is coated through.
Stir in hot cooked noodles and cheese.
Toss and cook until cheese is melted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve.

title: three cheese-ham puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2-quart round casserole. Beat eggs with hand beater.
Beat in baking mix and milk until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole. Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: parmesan onion bake
directions: Saute onions and celery until tender in a large skillet in 3 T butter; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan, melt the remaining butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk and bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 minutes until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over vegetables and toss to coat.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop up artichoke hearts.
Mix all together and bake at 400° until bubbly (gets a little brown on top, too).
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with dippers.
You need to have fairly firm crackers.
Triscuits or Wheat Thins work well.
(I usually use fresh Parmesan cheese, not the canned.
It's tastier!)

title: confucious almond cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, ground nuts,
1/4 cup sugar and brown sugar, then cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Form the mixture into a ball and knead until smooth.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles.
Place 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Lightly sprinkle with the additional sugar, then lightly press a whole nut in the center of each cookie.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: banana crunch bread
directions: In small bowl, combine melted margarine and frosting mix until crumbly.
Set aside.
In large bowl, blend sour cream with eggs and bananas, then blend in cake mix for 2 minutes.

title: turtle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup of condensed milk over low heat.
Spread evenly over pastry shell.
Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat.
Beat eggs with remainder of condensed milk, water, vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate mixture; mix well.
Pour over caramels.
Top with pecans.
Bake 35 minutes or until center is set.
Cool and chill before serving.

title: baked chow mein chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Place chow mein noodles in a plastic storage bag; crush noodles. Combine crushed noodles & nuts in shallow dish. Melt butter in microwave. Add soy sauce, ginger, & pepper to butter; stir to combine. Dip chicken breasts in butter mixture, then roll in noodles. Gently press noodle mixture onto chicken. Lay in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake 25-30 minutes or until juices run clear when pierced with a fork.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese; pour into a greased casserole.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Then add other ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a greased pan (cast iron skillet works well).
Then spread on the cheese.
Pour the rest of the mixture.
Bake in a 375 degree oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: hot dog cooler
directions: Mix juices and water; stir.
Add grape juice and stir.
After all ingredients are well blended, chill.
Store in large jugs until well chilled.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake and crumble corn bread, combine with onions, radishes, peppers and tomatoes.
Mix well mayonnaise, cucumber salad dressing and mustard. Pour over corn bread mixture and toss.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise; remove seeds and wash. Combine beef, cooked rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce. Pile mixture into peppers in large baking dish. Pour sauce over each pepper. Cover tightly and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 and 1/4 hours or until peppers are tender, basting occasionally. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy top crust for fruit pie
directions: Make pie filling using any fruit or berries, following recipe for regular pie.
Put into deep-dish bottom crust.

title: chicken sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into patties and fry in lightly greased pan until brown.

title: christmas boiled custard
directions: Put milk in double boiler and when thoroughly heated, add eggs, sugar and salt which have been previously mixed together. Cook approximately 10 minutes or longer, stirring constantly.
Do not overcook as milk will curdle.
Custard is done when it coats a wooden spoon.
Add vanilla to taste.
My dad usually added something a little stronger.
Chill as cold as possible.
Also, good over vanilla ice cream.

title: congealed tuna salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water for 5 minutes. Dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add gelatin to bouillon cubes.
Add tuna, mayonnaise, celery, olives and boiled eggs.
Chill in your favorite mold or in a small bowl.

title: marinated shrimp kabobs
directions: Toss shrimp and artichoke hearts with French dressing.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before grilling.
Drain marinade off and reserve. Thread shrimp and artichoke hearts alternately on 6-inch wooden skewers.
Grill over coals until done to taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: *caramels
directions: Mix together all ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil. Continue to cook until 250° on candy thermometer is ready, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
When cool, cut into individual squares and wrap individually in wax paper.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.
This recipe can be doubled.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: rhubaba
directions: In oven, melt butter in an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish; stir in brown sugar.
Top evenly with rhubarb.
If desired, add a few drops of red food coloring to sherry; drizzle over rhubarb.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, Karo, butter and salt in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil without stirring on medium heat to soft boil stage.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add vanilla, beat until mixture starts to lose its gloss, about 8 minutes.
Stir in cherries and nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart container suitable for microwave oven, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir.
Return to oven and microwave on High for 4 more minutes.
Remove from oven; stir in butter and vanilla.

Return to oven and microwave on High 2 more minutes. Remove from oven and quickly stir in baking soda (mixture will be light and foamy) and pour onto a lightly greased baking sheet or marble slab, spreading thin.
When cool, break into small pieces. Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 pound.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: potato elegante
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Cook in salted water until almost tender.
Drain.

title: hamburger crunch
directions: Saute onion and ground beef.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients except noodles.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Take pan from oven and sprinkle with a 6-ounce can of chow mein noodles.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mrs. mcmullan's fruit cake(from the files of dessie bell hayes)
directions: Chop everything good.
Using both hands, mix and mix until all mixed good.
Makes 2 loaves.
Put wax paper in pans and press cake until well packed.
Place in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Test to see if it sticks together.
If it does, remove from oven.
Let cool. When cooled, remove from pan and remove wax paper.
Wrap in a cloth soaked with grape juice or wine.
Store for future use.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; mix well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead three or four times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until tops are golden. Yields 14 biscuits.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add eggs, margarine, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into deep-dish pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 3/4 hours.
Pie is done when small knife inserted in pie comes out clean.

title: chinese dinner
directions: On large skillet, crumble hamburger meat and cook until brown. In another saucepan, cook Ramen noodles as directed on package. When hamburger and noodles are done, pour noodles in hamburger and mix.
Now mix 2 to 3 cans mixed vegetables into meat and noodles. No need to cook any longer.
Delicious with soy sauce.

title: parmesan oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing; dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken, bone side down, in a 9 x 13 inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to an hour, or until tender.
Six servings at about 197 calories per serving.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in kettle until tender.
Add flour; cook and stir until bubbly.
Gradually add chicken broth; cook and stir until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in the milk, cream, basil, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add vegetables; cook until heated through.

title: spicy roasted southern pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Melt butter and place in a mixing bowl. Add Worcestershire, hot sauce or pepper sauce, pepper and salt. Whisk together. Add pecans and stir to coat thoroughly. Pour nuts out onto a jellyroll pan and spread into a single layer. Place in oven and bake for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Drain on paper towels if necessary. Store in an airtight container. Can be made in advance.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Take breasts and put 2 slices of ham and 2 slices of cheese in the middle.
Fold and put toothpicks in to hold together.
Bake in oven in foiled pan at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: souped-up delmonicos
directions: Brown steaks seasoned with desired amounts of salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Add oregano, soup and milk.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: black forest cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Mix pie filling and almond flavoring.
While cake is still warm, poke top with fork and spread cherry filling over cake. While cake cools, prepare pudding, adding extra vanilla flavoring. Fold in whipped topping.
Spread pudding mixture over cake, carefully covering cherry pie filling.
Decorate with chocolate sprinkles and cherries.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in lukewarm water.
Mix other ingredients with yeast.
Mix dough thoroughly.
Flatten on a lightly floured surface and cut out into rounds with a biscuit cutter. Place into a
greased
pan and let stand 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Pour in spaghetti sauce and rice.
Simmer until rice is done.
Steam cabbage, then layer meat sauce, cabbage and cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together.

title: homemade pizza for kids
directions: Mix dough by directions on package.
Grease cake pans or any size pan you want to use.
Separate dough and grease hands before patting out on pan.
Top with whatever you like.
Add cheeses and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
This is fun to do when friends are over.
Everyone has their own pizza the way they like it.
(One package dough makes 2 pizzas usually.)

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry). Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Pour over prepared crust.
Combine nuts with reserved crumb mixture; sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool and chill.
Cut into bars.
Store, covered in refrigerator.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix meal and sugar; add beaten eggs and butter.
Stir in vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shells. Set aside for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp cheese balls
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add next 6 ingredients; stir until well blended.
Divide cheese mixture in half; form each half into a ball.
Sprinkle each cheese ball with paprika.
Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with crackers or cocktail bread.
Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: celery casserole
directions: Boil celery for 8 minutes.
Pour in greased baking dish with water chestnuts.
Mix milk with soup and pour over celery.
Brown bread crumbs in butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: moist apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples; let dissolve.
Add flour, egg, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into a well greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking make sauce.

title: vegetable shrimp and pasta
directions: In a large skillet, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and garlic; saute 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Remove.
Add water, wine, soup mix, oregano and dried red pepper to skillet.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes.
Return shrimp to skillet; simmer 2 minutes. Spoon over pasta; toss to coat.
Serves 4.

title: wrapped veggies with ranch dressing
directions: Cut veggies into strips 1/4 x 3-inch.
Wrap each strip in won ton wrap.
Seal end with water and cornstarch mixture.
When all are wrapped, heat oil for frying.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve with Ranch dressing.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In a food processor bowl with meat blade or blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover; blend 30 seconds. Refrigerate several
hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: grilled eggplant
directions: Preheat grill.
Combine olive oil and garlic in a bowl.
Cut onions and eggplant into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Brush with garlic oil mixture.
Grill for about 4 minutes on each side.
Baste with remaining garlic oil.
Season with sea salt.

title: el gando
directions: Brown meat; add salt, pepper and garlic salt or powder to taste. Add canned tomatoes and chili mix. Cook yellow rice according to package directions. Mix meat mixture and rice.
Put in large Pyrex dish. Heat cheese soup and milk; pour over meat and rice. Mix onions, olives, lettuce, fresh tomatoes and grated cheese together. Sprinkle over casserole. Top with crushed Fritos.

title: oma's squash casserole
directions: Mix onion and chicken soup well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add squash that has been cooked in salt water and mashed.
Mix well and add sugar.
Pour into well greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese and crushed ritz crackers.
Melt butter and pour over top. Bake covered for 45 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: microwave rocky road candy
directions: Cook chocolate chips and butter on High for 2 to 3 minutes; stir.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into buttered pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: frozen christmas salad
directions: Prepare whipped topping according to package directions. Combine all ingredients.
Place in square non-glass container. Freeze.

title: yum! yum! salad
directions: Mix crushed pineapple, sugar and juice of 3 lemons.
Bring to a boil.
Mix 1/2 cup water and gelatin.
Stir into mixture and boil 2 minutes; then set aside to cool.
Whip the whipping cream and add cheese.
Stir in cool mixture.
Tint color desired.

title: four bean salad
directions: Mix beans, sprouts, green pepper and onion in large bowl. Mix sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt and pepper together and pour over veggies.
Refrigerate until served.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together all ingredients except cheese. Pour half of the batter in large baking dish or pan, then add Cheddar cheese. Pour remaining batter on top of cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until brown.

title: tater sticks
directions: Dip potato wedges into melted margarine; shake with seasoning mix in plastic bag, coating well.
Place skin side down on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt cheeses in double boiler (can be melted in a microwave). Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Serve while hot with crackers.

title: christmas holly
directions: In saucepan, melt butter or margarine and marshmallows over low heat; stir constantly.
When melted, remove from heat.
Add food coloring; stir in corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper to look like holly leaves.
Decorate with cinnamon drops to look like holly berries.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Skin breasts and cut meat off bones. Cut in large bite size pieces.
Mix orange juice and milk together. Dip chicken pieces, then coat generously with flour. Cook in oil about 2-inches deep. Chop green onions.
Put chicken in bowl.
Cover with cashews and onions. Pour on gravy.

title: italian christmas pie(calsoune)
directions: My mom's special Christmas Eve pie.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add vinegar and orange juice. Mix well. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Add beets to the sauce. Serve hot or cold.

title: m&m super cookies
directions: Coarsely grind 1 1/2 cups of M&M's.
Reserve the rest for decoration.
Beat oleo and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped candies and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake 9 to 11 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl combine Eagle Brand and water.
Add pudding mix, beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.
In a large bowl, spoon in 1/3 pudding mixture, add 1/3 vanilla wafers, and 1 banana. Continue layering, ending with pudding mixture.

title: whiskey balls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add whiskey. Form into small balls. Roll each ball in additional powdered sugar. Store in covered container.

title: soup mixture
directions: Chop and measure all vegetables.
Place in open kettle with sugar and salt.
Cook until thick.
Pour at once into hot jars and process 1 1/2 hours.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Put sauerkraut on bottom of dish or pan.
Add noodles.
Mix soup, mustard and mayonnaise.
Spread over noodles.
Add onions, corned beef and cheese.

title: percolator punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in the bottom of a 6-cup glass percolator.
(Use glass or plastic; metal will ruin the punch. Yes, it is worth it to borrow a pot!)
Place spices in basket of percolator.
Let the mixture come to a full perk.
Let perk 3 minutes.
Keep warm until served.

title: herbed rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart pan.
Heat to boiling; stir well.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: white bread
directions: Combine 1 cup boiling water and milk in a bowl.
Add 3 teaspoons sugar and margarine, mixing well.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add to milk mixture and mix well.
Set aside.

title: mashed potato rolls
directions: Place mixture in a greased bowl to rise (about 3 hours). Work down and shape into favorite shape.
Brush with butter and let rise again.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: Heat rice and 2 cups milk to boil; stir constantly.
Reduce heat; cover.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add vanilla pudding and 3/4 cup milk.
Mix well.
Stir into rice mixture.
Bring to boil.
Stir constantly.
Add raisins and nutmeg.
Pour into serving dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Beat first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and whip for 10 minutes or so. Pour into baked crust. Sprinkle remaining crust on top.
Chill and serve.

title: margarita de largo
directions: Shake and pour in 8 ounce footed glass.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour one-piece tube pan. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, boiling coffee, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool and ice with milk chocolate icing.

title: peanut butter cake squares
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and peanuts; press into baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and 1 cup nondairy topping. Spread this over crust.
Mix chocolate, vanilla puddings and milk. Pour over cream cheese and chill until firm.
Top with remaining topping.
Grate milk chocolate over top and sprinkle with peanuts; chill and serve.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: In large roasting pan, place tenderloin.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a bowl, mix thoroughly.
Pour marinate sauce over meat; marinate for 4 to 6 hours.
Then bake for one hour at 350° uncovered.	Make sure internal heat reaches 150° temperature inside.

title: myra's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add eggs, oleo. Mix saltine cracker crumbs, onions, and milk.
Let cook softer and add to squash.
Mix chicken soup with water until smooth.
Add to squash.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° until slightly brown, about 30 minutes.

title: carrie's cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; pour sugar, salt and lemon juice over cranberries.
Mix and let stand 2 hours.
Mix jello with boiling water.
When cool and syrupy, add to cranberries, nuts and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
This salad may be frozen.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix all
together.
Bake
at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Combine seasoning mix, water and chicken in large skillet. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Spoon filling into bottom of each taco shell. Top with lettuce, cheese and tomatoes.

title: baked yellow squash
directions: Cut up squash and boil until tender.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Mash squash in medium bowl.
Add onion, cheese, milk, part of cracker crumbs and egg.
Put in buttered casserole dish and sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla and mix lightly, but well.
Combine the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon and add to egg mixture.
Stir until blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: see's fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar.
Bring to rolling boil and boil 10 minutes.
Put chips, nuts, Marshmallow Creme, margarine and vanilla in large bowl.
Pour milk mixture over all and stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine vinegar, garlic salt and salad dressing; blend thoroughly.
Combine other ingredients, then add salad dressing mixture and toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly for best flavor. Serves 8.

title: turkey ranchero
directions: Cut each thigh in half; remove bone and skin.
Place in slow cooker.
Combine dry enchilada sauce mix with tomato paste and water.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread over turkey thighs.
Cover. Cook on low 7 to 8 hours or until tender.
Turn pot on high.
Add cheese; stir until cheese melts.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter; saut onion in butter. Mix all ingredients together; stir in potatoes. Pour into 8 1/2 x 13 Pyrex dish. Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup butter. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: susie's salad
directions: Cut up vegetables and marinate overnight all together in a closed container.
When ready to serve, mix together Miracle Whip, sour cream and Italian seasoning mix.
Mix vegetables and seasoning mixture.
Serve.

title: easy one dish spaghetti
directions: In a 10-inch skillet with cover, saute vegetables and ground beef in oil.
Add spaghetti, spreading over beef mixture.
Mix tomatoes, catsup and seasonings.
Pour over spaghetti, making sure spaghetti is covered with liquid.
Cover and cook over medium heat (simmer) for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: leather britches or shuck beans
directions: Wash and dry a batch of firm green beans.
Remove ends and strings.
Using a large darning needle with heavy white thread, push the needle through the bean pod near the middle of each, pushing them along the thread so that they are about 1/4 inch apart.
Hang up the strings of beans in a warm, well ventilated place to dry.
They will shrivel and turn greenish gray.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook, bone and chop chicken.
Cook rice.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Turn into 3-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to boil.
Take off heat and store in container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion in 4 tablespoons margarine until tender, do not brown.
Mix soup with Cheez Whiz and milk.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cook in pressure cooker for 15 minutes the fish, onions, potatoes and celery.
Then
add tomatoes and margarine.
Simmer until done.

title: swifty beans
directions: Put beans in crock-pot on high.
Mix vinegar, brown sugar, onions and fried bacon in large skillet.
Bring to boil; simmer for 1 minute.
Pour over beans in crock-pot; cook for about 1 or 2 hours on medium.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 1 large loaf or 12 small individual ones.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain off fat. Add 1 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup vinegar and 1 teaspoon mustard. Stir.
Pour over loaf and bake 20 more minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand and egg yolks at low speed.
Slowly add juice, mixing until homogeneous.
Pour into baked shell. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: easy chicken gumbo
directions: Heat butter in a 3-quart saucepan until melted.
Add okra, onion and green pepper; cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir in broth, tomatoes with liquid, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in chicken and parsley; heat through.
Serve chicken mixture over hot rice.

title: spinach and treet casserole
directions: Break or cut all solid ingredients into small pieces.
Mix ingredients, except eggs, milk, flour, black pepper and garlic salt.
Put spinach mixture in greased casserole dish.
Pour milk and egg mixture over spinach mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours or until firm and brown.

title: juanita's quick mexican chicken
directions: Follow directions on Rice-A-Roni box to prepare rice, but substitute chili-style tomatoes for recipe on box.
Meanwhile, while rice is cooking, slice chicken thinly into strips about 3 inches long.
Saute strips in a 10-inch saute pan or wok with oil until golden brown.
Don't crowd the pan.
Saute the chicken in batches, if necessary.
Use a slotted spoon to remove to a platter and keep warm in a 200° oven.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine broccoli, mushrooms, water chestnuts, onion and dressing in a large bowl.
Cover and marinate several hours, stirring occasionally.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Cook fresh asparagus in boiling, salted water for 5 to 6 minutes (or cook frozen according to package directions).
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream, carrots, onion and pepper.
Fold in asparagus.
Turn mixture into a 1-quart baking dish.

title: chicken feed
directions: In skillet, saute onion, mushrooms, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon thyme in the margarine.
Stir in the chicken, gravy, bouillon and pepper; spoon into a greased casserole and remaining thyme.
Spoon over mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix together butter, 1/2 cup powered sugar and vanilla. Mix in flour, salt and nuts. Best to chill this dough for 1 hour in the refrigerator. Once chilled, shape into 1 inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 - 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm and then again once they are cool.

title: pasta trivera
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil.
Add salt and spaghetti; boil 7 to 8 minutes.
Heat 1/3 cup olive oil in saucepan.
Add garlic and cook slowly for 3 minutes.
Stir in parsley and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Put off the heat and stir in walnuts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Stir together in large bowl: flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
Stir together pumpkin, oil, and water in another bowl.
Add eggs, beaten well. Make a well in center of flour mixture and stir in pumpkin mixture just until dough is moistened.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until bread taste done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Mix beans, barbecue sauce, raisins, sugar, onion and apple together in a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with bacon. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for one hour.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon. Stir in oats, sugar and raisins.
Add applesauce, oil, eggs and milk. Stir only until dry ingredients are blended.
Fill a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan half full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Cool.
Wrap cooled bread; store one day before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sweet and sour german pork chops
directions: Drain juice from sauerkraut.
Place in bottom of oblong baking dish.
Place pork chops over kraut.
Mix and pour over top the tomato soup, water and brown sugar.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans and drain.
Melt cheese and soup over low heat and add to beans.
Add 1/2 can of French fried onions and stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add other half on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and sour cream in mixing bowl.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into ice trays without sections to freeze. Serve on lettuce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Cook apples and other ingredients in apple juice until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Pour into a 10-inch pie crust.
Put slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° until brown, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in peaches and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased, 2-quart casserole.
Keep peach mixture hot in oven.
Put shortening into flour.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto hot peach mixture.
Bake until topping is golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm, and if desired, top with whipped cream.

title: sour salmon and noodles
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Coat macaroni with butter. Pour in bowls and top with salmon mixture.

title: french toast
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Dip bread, one at a time, in egg mixture; turn to coat evenly.
Fry until lightly brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Serve with syrup or jelly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and beat eggs, sugar and salt together.
Add Karo and pecans alternately.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at a low temperature (350°) until done.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, milk, salt and pepper. Shape into balls.
Fry until brown.

title: mrs. wealand's molasses drop cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Before putting in oven, beat an egg and brush on top of each cookie.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix everything together in one container.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: martha's soup
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook for 5 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts, about 20 minutes.

title: hearty cauliflower soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook cauliflower and carrots in water until tender; set aside (do not drain).
In a skillet over medium heat, brown the sausage and onion, drain.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add the milk; bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add cauliflower, carrots and cooking liquid; heat through.
Stir in the cheese until melted.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas and set aside.
Cream
sugar
and oil.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift
dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, bananas, nuts and dry ingredients to
sugar
and oil mixture.
Mix well. Bake in loaf pan about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: white trash
directions: Mix all ingredients except almond bark or candiquick in a large bowl.
Melt almond bark or candiquick.
Pour over all ingredients. Mix well.
Pour out on 2 long pieces of wax paper (30 to 36-inches).
Spread evenly and thin.
Let cool for about an hour, then break into pieces.
Store in large covered containers.
Makes 2 (one gallon) jars full.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Dice green pepper, onion, celery and pimentos into small pieces.
Combine with wet ingredients.
Add drained peas and beans. Chill.
The longer it sets the better it tastes.

title: grandma welch's sweet potato pone
directions: Separate egg yolks and whites.
Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat whites until stiff and fold in potato mixture.
Bake in a buttered dish for about 45 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: cot's recipe
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Add peanut butter and blend thoroughly.
Pour over the cornflakes.
Stir until well coated. Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked eggplant a la wyatt's cafeteria
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1 inch cubes and soak in salt water in refrigerator overnight (minimum of 6 hours).
Drain eggplant and place in pan.
Cover with water and simmer until tender.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onions, green peppers, and celery in melted butter for about 15 minutes or until tender.
Combine cooked eggplant, bread crumbs, and sauteed vegetables.
Add eggs, pimento, and seasoning; blend thoroughly.
Place in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together 5 cups flour and lard.
Add 1 cup flour, milk and salt.
Roll out on floured surface.

title: triple chocolate pie
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine chocolate fudge pudding mix with 1 1/4 cups milk. Mix with a wire whisk until well combined and thickened. Pour mixture into pie crust and refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in 9-inch square baking pan.
Add water. Combine dry ingredients.
Using a pastry blender, cut in butter until butter particles are fine as in biscuits.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.

title: tripe soup
directions: Wash tripe in water and vinegar.
Season tripe with salt and pepper.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Cook in 1/2 pot water for 1 1/2 hours or pressure cook for 1/2 hour.
Add onion, cabbage, pumpkin and other vegetables; season to taste.
Add spaghetti 30 minutes before the soup is finished cooking.
If the soup is too thick, add a little water and season to taste.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Mix with pineapple.
Add butter or margarine and cook until thick.
Stir while cooking as it sticks easily.
Let cool before using.
Line bottoms and sides of pie shells with sliced bananas.
Sprinkle pecans over bananas. Add
pineapple
mixture
and cover with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: dietetic fruit cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Must be refrigerated.

title: doris' pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour and brown sugar, cut in butter and oleo until it resembles crumbs. Press crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
While it bakes, combine eggs, sugar and syrup, salt and vanilla.
Blend well; stir in pecan pieces and pour over golden, hot crust.
Reduce heat to 275°.
Bake until center is set.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, soda, spice, salt and baking powder.
In second bowl, mix remaining ingredients well.
Add both together until moistened.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans to cooling racks.

title: prune cake
directions: Flour and grease tube pan. Mix with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Springs back when touched.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine until golden brown.
Melt 1/4 cup of butter or margarine in a container. The microwave is good for this.
Add 30 crumbled crackers.
Put the butter and cracker mixture in a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish, covering the bottom of the dish.
Next, place the hot sauteed onions on top of the cracker mixture, then place cheese over the onions.
Next, scald milk in a saucepan.
Add to it 3 beaten eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese and onions.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean like custard.

title: creamy turkey soup
directions: Bring turkey broth to a boil in a large pot.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery and cook for about 20 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.
Add leftover turkey, green onions, salt, pepper, thyme and sage; stir well and return to a boil.
Cook over medium heat for another 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix evaporated milk and flour in a mixing bowl with an electric mixer.
Blend milk mixture into soup.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened (approximately 8 to 10 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: beef and onion cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese and chopped corned beef.
Add chopped onion and onion powder. Form into ball and chill.
For larger ball, double ingredients.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Drain cocktail and mix with other ingredients.

title: cool fruit tart
directions: Mix Bisquick and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Mix in egg until soft dough forms.
Spray fruit tart pan with Pam.
Work dough toward edges.
Prick with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° until brown.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter and flour, in a pot; bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes. Blend butter with flour; add to the corn. Mix well and remove from heat.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Garnish with shredded carrots, if desired.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Make a paste of red coloring and cocoa.
Add to cream mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix buttermilk in same cup as coloring.
Use all clinging coloring. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to mixture; beat well. Fold in vinegar.
Pour into 2 cake pans lined with greased wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pear bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; make well in center of mixture. Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry mixture.
Stir until just moistened,
Spoon into two well greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix together and put in greased 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Wrap and roll in wax paper and put in freezer until hardened.
Slice and bake at 375° until light brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Add Flour, shortening and salt.
Mix together and then add next four ingredients.
Mix can be frozen.
Makes 3- 9 inch pies. Bake at 350 degrees.

title: brown rice
directions: Place dry rice in casserole dish.
Pour in beef broth and water.
Put in stick of butter.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chicken breasts in mustard sauce
directions: Heat margarine or butter in 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Add chicken breasts.
Cook for 12 to 14 minutes, turning after 6 minutes or until juices run clear.
Remove chicken and reserve. Add onion and brandy or apple juice to skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Stir in whipping cream, parsley and mustard.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add chicken and walnuts.
Heat until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sarah's chili
directions: Combine ingredients; simmer for 1 hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine first 5 ingredients, stirring well. Spoon mixture into a greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish. Combine cracker crumbs and butter, stirring well. Sprinkle mixture evenly over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, oil and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine sugar, cocoa and water; pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken  salad
directions: Poach chicken in broth with next 5 ingredients 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Salt to taste; cool in broth; debone and chop fine.
Blend chicken with 1 cup mayonnaise.
Add next 3 ingredients and season to taste.
Fold in eggs and add additional mayonnaise until mixture reaches desired consistency.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: mom's strawberry pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to directions; set aside to cool. Slice enough fresh berries to line bottom of pie shell.
Save several berries with hulls on for garnish.
Cut remaining berries into a saucepan; add sugar and cook on medium heat.
Stir.
Put cornstarch in small bowl; add some liquid from saucepan.
Stir until well mixed and return to saucepan.
Stir until mixture thickens and pour into pie shell.
Cool.
Cover with whipped cream.
Garnish with whole berries.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: ugly shonton meat balls
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well and form into balls.
Brown gently, add wine.
Simmer until wine is evaporated.
Add soup mixed with milk.
Simmer until sauce is down to about half.

title: quick country pie
directions: Melt butter and add chocolate chips.
Heat until chips are melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut crunch delight
directions: In a bowl, combine the margarine, flour, coconut, sugar and almonds.
Press lightly into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown, stirring every 10 minutes to form coarse crumbs.
Cool.
Divide crumbs mixture in half.
Press half into same baking pan.
In a mixing bowl, combine pudding mixes and milk.
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon over the crust and top with remaining crumbs.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt the 2 tablespoons of butter; add the chopped mushrooms and green pepper.
Stir and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add flour, salt and paprika and cook until frothy.
Add cream and cook until it thickens.
Add chicken and set aside over hot water.
Beat egg yolks and 1/4 cup butter, onion and lemon juice.
Stir into the other mixture and cook a few minutes.
Serve on waffles or toast.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring to boil last 7 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: virginia pickles
directions: Make a brine of a proportion of 2 cups salt to one gallon water; boil and pour over cucumbers boiling hot.
Let stand one week.
In hot weather, skim daily.
Drain and cut in chunks or slice.
For the next 3 mornings, make a boiling hot solution of one tablespoon powdered alum and one gallon water and pour over the pickles.
Each morning drain the pickles and make the solution fresh.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa and food coloring and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Beat in cocoa and food coloring mixture.
Divide mixture evenly between 3 (9-inch) round greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Lay crescent rolls out on baking dish or cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.
Let cool completely.
Mix together cream cheese, mayo and Hidden Valley.
Spread on cool crescent rolls.
Top with chopped vegetables.

title: chess pie
directions: When eggs are half beaten, add flour and beat until smooth. Stir in sugar and salt.
Add melted butter, vanilla and milk (in that order).
Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling liquid.
Pour in 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.
Cut into shapes.

title: spinach and lettuce salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and sugar and pour over the spinach and lettuce, bacon and onion.
Mix well.

title: baked rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt half the butter in a heavy saucepan, cook the onion and garlic, until the onion is translucent.
Add the rice and stir briefly, until the rice is coated with butter.
Stir in broth and spices.
Cover with a loose fitting lid and place in oven.
Bake exactly 17 minutes.
Discard parsley and thyme sprigs and bay leaf and serve.

title: mushrooms & chicken livers
directions: Cook livers, covered in butter until almost tender. (about 10 mins.) Add mushrooms and green onions, cook until onions and livers are tender. combine remaining ingredients and add to livers. Heat and stir just until sauce is hot. Serve over rice or hot buttered toast.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Mix the cottage cheese and mayonnaise together, then add the dry dressing mix.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Heat and pour over gelatin.
Let cool.
Add Cokes and cherries.
When gelatin is slightly thick, add cheese, fruit and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let chill until firm before serving.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat together margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Stir in vanilla, peel and zucchini.
Alternately stir in dry ingredients and milk.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Turn out.
May drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.

title: apricot salad
directions: Boil water and sugar; put in Jell-O.
Stir well.
Stir in pineapple, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add nuts and celery (if so desired).
Refrigerate.
Quick and good.

title: tomato casserole
directions: In greased baking dish, layer tomatoes (by overlapping), onion, cheese and dressing mix.
Continue layering ingredients ending with cheese and dressing crumbs on top.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend milk and peanut butter until smooth. Mix in crumbs and chocolate pieces.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until set.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: paprikas potatoes
directions: Melt shortening.
Add paprika and sliced potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook over medium flame.
Gradually add water until done, about 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding ground beef last.
Pack firmly in loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fettuccine casserole
directions: Cook pasta accordingly.
Meanwhile, in saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Blend in cheese; stir in whipping cream.
Heat almost to boiling, stirring constantly, with whisk.
Place eggs in a small bowl and beat slightly.
Stir small amount of hot cream mixture into saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, with whisk until thoroughly heated, about 5 minutes.
Stir in bacon and parsley.
Toss sauce with hot pasta.
Serve immediately.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas pound cake
directions: Beat shortening until creamy; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° in ungreased tube pan.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Cut carrots diagonally into 1/4 slices.
Cook carrots in boiling water for 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Keep warm in a serving dish.
Combine next 4 ingredients in saucepan, gradually add orange juice, stirring well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly, pour over carrots; toss well.
Garnish if desired.

title: 2 layer pineapple-jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Pour thin layer (1/2-inch deep) into a 9 x 13-inch salad pan.
Let congeal.
When remainder of gelatin thickens, add marshmallows, pineapple and pecan pieces. Fold whipped topping in carefully; mix well.
Pour over congealed, clear gelatin layer.
Let congeal overnight.
When ready to serve, cut jello squares and turn salad, bottom side up, on shredded lettuce so clear red jello is on the top and creamy layer is on the bottom.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Slowly add milk and vanilla. Then cook slowly until done.

title: sauce piquant with italian sausage
directions: First you make a roux.
When the roux is dark brown, add chopped onions, pepper and celery and continue cooking.
When onions become clear, add green onions and parsley and continue cooking a few minutes.
Add a bit of cold water so that roux becomes a thick liquid.
Add garlic and rest of seasonings, including tomato sauce and wine.
Add sausage and cover with water about 2 inches over the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently, being sure that you have enough water so that sauce piquant won't stick.
Cook for several hours until meat is tender.
Serve over spaghetti or rice or just about anything or by itself.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook the chicken in enough water to cover. Add the bay leaf, garlic, chopped onion, celery tops and basil. When chicken is done (1 to 2 hours), drain and let cool. Remove from bones and dice. Add the remaining ingredients.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in order and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°F.
Melt margarine in shallow baking dish while oven is heating.
Add chicken and sprinkle both sides with soy sauce and sesame seeds.

title: florida pie
directions: Crush the bananas.
Drain pineapple.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Combine with soups, broth and chilies. Add pieces of chicken and mix well.
In large baking dish, place a layer of tortillas, chicken and cheese.
Repeat layers until casserole is filled, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (Better if sets a couple of hours before baking, can also be frozen.)
Serves 8.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Use no salt or pepper.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: In large saucepan, over medium heat, bring cranberries, sugar and juice to a boil, stir frequently.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or up to a week before using.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Butter a 2 1/2-quart casserole or larger if available. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Saute onion and pepper in butter; drain.
Heat soup and broth until hot.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour; after 30 minutes, stir and continue cooking.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine butter and onion in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong baking dish.
Microwave, uncovered, at power level High for 4 to 5 minutes or until onion is fairly soft, stirring once.
Add beef, mushrooms and seasonings.
Microwave, uncovered, at power level High for 9 to 10 minutes, or until beef is cooked, stirring twice.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in peanut butter, then flour.
Pour into two lightly greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until centers test done.
After about 15 minutes of baking, sprinkle peanuts onto batter to five a crunchy topping. Serve with whipped cream and a sprinkle of peanuts, if desired. Makes 2 loaves, 12 servings each.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat together the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Start with 1 cup sifted flour.
Add milk.
Add 1 more cup of flour.
Add sour cream; add remaining flour.
Stir in flavoring and margarine or butter.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first four ingredients.
Pour sugar over and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or longer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and simmer the first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with grated cheese and let come to bubble again.

title: cake
directions: Line baking pans with aluminum foil.
Use 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan or 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Have nuts and fruits ready and mixed.
Save some to decorate cake.

title: kid's special fruit-flavor popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in large bowl.
Add melted butter; toss to coat. Sprinkle with gelatin; toss until evenly coated.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Bring to a rolling boil sugar and milk.
Cook 7 minutes.
Add margarine, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour over yellow cake.

title: cindy's meat and potatoes
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Add to hamburger.
Sprinkle on chili powder; stir and add tomato sauce. Cover with water and heat to a boil.
Then switch to medium heat and cover 30 to 45 minutes.

title: noodles and beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion, soup, juice, bouillon cubes and water Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add more water if necessary.
Add noodles and cook until noodles are tender.
Add salt, pepper and sour cream.
Heat gently.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley before serving.

title: no bake peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in a saucepan and let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove; add last 3 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Allow to cool, then eat.

title: colorful six-bean salad
directions: Combine all beans and scallions in a large bowl; stir to mix. Combine olive oil, egg yolk, vinegar, sugar, garlic and pepper in container of an electric blender.
Process at low speed until well blended.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 4 hours.
To serve, spoon bean salad onto lettuce-lined salad plate; garnish with quarters of hard-cooked eggs.
Yields 12 servings.

title: johnny cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine, pecans, coconut and vanilla together.
Roll into small balls and place on a wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator.
In a double boiler melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Take a toothpick and dip each chocolate ball in chocolate mixture.
Twist toothpick to remove. One toothpick will do a whole recipe.
Makes about 60 pieces.

title: candy cane cafe white bread
directions: Put yeast in 2 cups warm water and set aside.
Put 5 pounds flour in a large container.
Mix in sugar and salt.
Add shortening and mix well until it feels like corn meal, no chunks of shortening.
Throw a pinch of sugar and flour into yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups water to flour mixture; add the yeast water too.
Mix well, cover and let rise overnight.

title: chocolate bubble biscuits(makes 16 biscuits)
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Using pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in 1/3 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in chocolate morsels. Add milk; stir until dough holds a shape.
On floured board, knead dough lightly.
Roll dough into 16 balls.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt remaining 1/3 cup butter.
Pour 1/2 cup of melted butter in 8-inch square baking pan.
In cup, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/3 cinnamon sugar mixture over butter in baking pan.
Place dough balls in single layer in pan.
Brush with remaining melted butter.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: marge's whipped potatoes
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes.
Add butter, sour cream, cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend together and pour into large casserole.
Sprinkle with Lawry's or paprika.
Refrigerate until needed then bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Wonderful for holiday dinner.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a casserole dish.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl, combine apples, milk and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, cut 1/2 cup oleo into 1 cup biscuit mix until crumbly.
Stir in apple mixture.

title: pan-fish with green onions and mushrooms
directions: Dredge the fish in a mixture of cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Fry fish in 2 tablespoons butter until browned on each side.
Transfer to a dish.
Saute mushrooms and capers in another skillet in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and remove them to a lightly buttered shallow baking dish.
Saute the onions and garlic in butter for 1 to 2 minutes.
Lay the fish on the bed of mushrooms, sprinkle with bread crumbs mixed with tarragon and spread the onions, garlic and chives over this.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: In mixing bowl, mix first 4 ingredients by hand.
Bring to a boil and add to above ingredients the margarine, oil, water and cocoa.
Mix together buttermilk and baking soda.
Add to flour mixture the eggs and vanilla.
Mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: little pizzas
directions: Mix together tomato paste, sugar, salt, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Spread thinly on muffins.
Sprinkle cheese over tomato mixture.
Top with sausage.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix
first
6 ingredients, starting with sweet potatoes in mixing
bowl.
Add	milk.
Fold
in
beaten
sweetened egg whites. Pour
into
pie
shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake until center is firm, approximately 40	minutes.
Nutmeg and sugar may be sprinkled on top of pie before baking, if desired.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Let cheese and margarine soften.
Mix well with hand mixer. Cut all crust off bread and cut into 2-inch squares.
Spread all sides with cheese mixture and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serve with cole slaw.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix and chill butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix and chill pudding mixes and milk.

title: pasta and sausage bake
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage; drain.
In a greased 2-quart baking dish, combine sausage, sauce, pasta and Parmesan cheese. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: "no peek" chicken
directions: Grease casserole.
Place rice, soup and water in casserole; mix well.
Place chicken over that and sprinkle with dried onion soup.
Seal tightly with aluminum foil or tight cover on casserole.
Bake in a 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk, stir in hot vegetables and cover with cheese.
Heat through.
Makes a large vegetable dish. Preparation time 10 minutes.

title: chicken 'n gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in 14 x 20-inch Reynolds oven bag (large size).
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Add gravy mix, garlic powder and water to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt and pepper.
Place in bag.
Place carrots and celery in bag around chicken.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top. Bake until chicken is tender, 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tina's coconut cake
directions: Cream together oleo or butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Mix well and add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add sour cream, cake flour, baking soda, coconut, almond extract, coconut extract and vanilla extract.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in tube pan.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend in egg.

Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture, gradually. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls (about 2 measuring tablespoons) of dough 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes. Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Measure oil into wok (or large skillet).
Add cabbage, turn heat to moderate and stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly until cabbage is tender but crisp, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix baking powder in salmon juice.
Mix salmon, egg and onion together with
fork.
Add
flour
and baking powder mixture.
Mix together
and
drop by spoonful into hot shortening and fry.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Brown, drain and crumble the bacon. Saute the onions in bacon fat.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper. Coarsely chop the cabbage and add to skillet. Add drained, chopped tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes. Add bacon. Simmer 10 more minutes.

title: irish soda bread(yield: 1 loaf)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: pain perdu(lost bread)
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar rapidly; continue to beat.
Add cornstarch and, when mixed, add milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Dip bread slice in mixture, coating each side thoroughly.
Use just enough oil to cover bottom of skillet and fry over moderate heat. Fry each slice until golden brown.
Serve hot, sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Mix and put in freezer until ready to serve.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Simmer ingredients, except eggs, for 5 minutes.
Pour over eggs in large jar.
Refrigerate for 3 days.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Pam a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Layer whipped cream.
Layer crushed Oreos.
Layer sliced bananas.
Repeat, ending with Oreos sprinkled on top.
Make in the morning to serve at night.
Best refrigerated 10 hours.

title: cake frosting
directions: Cook flour, milk and salt to a paste; let cool.
Beat shortening, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add together; beat. Add vanilla.

title: broccoli layered salad
directions: Layer in large bowl.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix well.
Finish filling gallon jug with water.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, vanilla and zucchini. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Remove chicken from bones; dice in buttered dish.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon butter on medium-low heat.
Add chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and diced, boiled eggs until ingredients are mixed well.
Pour over chicken in dish.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Melt marshmallows in hot milk. Add eggs and lemon juice.
Cook until thick; cool. Add whipped cream, pineapple, nuts and grapes. Chill. Makes 20 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken; butter dish.
Add onion, cheese, chips and chicken to dish.
Heat can of mushroom soup, chicken soup and 1/2 can Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan (well-greased) for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; wash and remove seed and white membrane. Mix ground beef and onion in 1 1/2-quart casserole and cook at Max power for 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Stir in salt, pepper, rice and half of the tomato sauce.
Fill pepper halves with mixture.
Place in glass dish.
Top each pepper with remaining sauce.
Cook, covered, at Max power for 8 to 10 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bisquick waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
One cup batter makes 4 square waffles. Recipe makes 12 individual waffles.
Club soda makes waffles crisp.

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend cheese, milk, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add sugar, beating until frosting is smooth and of spreading consistency.
If necessary, stir in additional milk, one tablespoon at a time. Before adding sugar, stir in chocolate; cool.

title: congealed vegetable salad
directions: Prepare gelatin with boiling water and cold water.
Add onion, salt and vinegar.
Blend and chill until slightly thickened (about 1 hour).
Add other ingredients, pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
While waiting, combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, spices and cheese in large bowl.
Mix well.
Drain macaroni and add to cheese mixture. Spoon into sprayed 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss with Miracle Whip.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water in saucepan over low heat until raisins are plump, 20 to 30 minutes. Drain liquid and add water to measure 1/2 cup.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Have ungreased cookie sheets ready.
Cream the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in raisin liquid.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to moist ingredients.
Mix well. Add oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful 2-inches apart on cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: blintz bubble ring
directions: Cut cream cheese into 20 pieces.
Roll into balls.
Roll each biscuit into a 3-inch circle.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1 cheese ball and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture in the center of each biscuit; pinch dough to seal.
Pour butter or margarine into the bottom of a 5-cup ring mold.
Sprinkle half of the nuts and half of remaining cinnamon mixture into mold.
Top with half of the rolls, placing seam side up.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until brown.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained pineapple in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer and spread.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cut butter in thin pats and put over top.
Serve warm or cold.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix fruit cocktail and eggs.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in microwave.
Mix in cereal.
Put in bag with almost a bag of powdered sugar and shake.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in 1 Tbsp. of the margarine till tender.
Combine egg, milk, 1/3 cup of the crushed crackers, and dash of pepper.
Stir in onion mixture and corn.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Melt remaining margarine; toss with remaining crumbs.
Sprinkle crumb mixture atop corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or till a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Makes 4 servings.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, brown sugar, egg yolk, orange peel and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and salt; stir into butter mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Slightly beat egg white with fork.
Dip balls in egg white; roll each in walnuts.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets; press thumb gently in center of each cookie.
Bake in upper third of oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool on wire racks.

title: pork chops hong-kong
directions: Brown chops, pour off fat.
Place chops in baking pan; arrange onion, mushrooms and water chestnuts on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: fancy popcorn(make your favorite flavor)
directions: Makes 3 quarts.
Use a 4 quart bowl.
In a large bowl, microwave butter and marshmallows on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Marshmallows will puff up.
Add gelatin and stir to blend.
Pour over popped corn and stir to coat corn.
Spread on buttered surface to dry.

title: pork chop meal
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops to taste.
Cook quickly in lightly greased skillet without flour until brown.
Layer as follows, pork chops, onion slices, pepper strips or rings, chopped celery, cooked rice and tomatoes.
Put lid on skillet and simmer 35 minutes.

title: mexicali pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops; season with salt and pepper.
Set aside. Reserve drippings in skillet.

title: stuffed baked potatoes-chicken(low-fat and cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes and prick in several places with a fork.
Bake in the center of the oven for 1 hour or until tender.
While potatoes are baking, place the chicken stock, onion and garlic in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove potatoes from oven and cut in half.
Scrape the pulp into a bowl, reserving the shells.
Add the chicken mix along with everything, except the Parmesan cheese.
Beat with a mixer until light and fluffy.
Stuff the potato mix back into the shells. Sprinkle with Parmesan and place back into the oven for 10 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and lemon caper cream
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add shallots and saute until lightly browned, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice and stir; scrape the bottom of the pan with wooden spoon to remove lumps and browned bits.
When most of juice evaporates, add cream.
Gently boil until thick, 10 to 12 minutes. Stir in capers and serve immediately over cooked pasta.
Garnish with parsley.

title: turkey rolls
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: chicken cilantro
directions: Heat oil; add turmeric and garlic and saute onion.
Add chicken, salt and pepper; lightly brown.
Add all water and chicken cubes; boil for 30 to 45 minutes, until chicken is tender. Add cilantro, green onions and potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are cooked.
Serve with rice and green salad or shred cooked chicken and serve with flour tortillas and beans.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese until well blended.
Stir in
remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with vegetable sticks.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook the noodles in chicken broth until done.
To this, add the soups.
Add chicken pieces and put in baking dish.
Top with Velveeta.
Sprinkle chili powder on top for color.
Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes more.

title: onion cheese strata
directions: Separate onion slices into rings. Trim crusts from bread. Place 4 slices of bread in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of cheese and onions.
Repeat.

title: cheesy garden mac salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
Mix macaroni with mayonnaise, condensed milk, vinegar and cheese.
Then add carrots, peppers and onion. Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: jerrie's brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken, until tender.
Debone and cut very fine (reserve broth).
Add all ingredients (except English peas) to broth.
Cook over low heat for 3 hours.
Add English peas the last 30 minutes of cooking.
This will stick, so stir often.

title: mrs. royal's chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
To the stock, add onions.
Cook until tender.
Add enough water to make 2 quarts.
Bring to a boil and drop in spaghetti.
Cook over high heat until tender.
Add tomato soup, pimento, celery, mushrooms and cooked, chopped chicken.
Cover and cook 1 hour; simmer.
Add cheese when ready to serve.

title: hobo bread
directions: In the evening, soak raisins in boiling water with baking soda; cover.
In the morning, add brown sugar, white sugar, oil and salt.
Add flour.
Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) coffee cans. Fill cans, dividing batter equally.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool a few minutes before removing from cans, then cool on wire rack.
Enjoy right away or wrap and freeze.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack in loaf pan or baking dish.
Spread with sauce.
Bake in 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: laurine's millionaire candy
directions: Microwave caramel and milk until melted, 2 minutes.
Stir and heat 2 more minutes.
If all is melted, add pecan halves; stir real good.
Drop by small spoon onto buttered aluminum foil until hardened.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler pan.
Dip caramel into chocolate; put back on aluminum foil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and take out bone, save broth.
Mix melted margarine and dressing.
Layer of dressing, layer of chicken in a casserole dish.
Pour over chicken cream of mushroom or celery soup mixed with 1 can of broth.
Another layer of dressing and layer of chicken then chicken soup mixed with 1 can of broth. Sprinkle rest of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: meal in one mexican salad
directions: Cook ground beef until brown. Add chopped onion; cook until tender. Stir in beans, French dressing, water, and chili powder. Simmer for 15 minutes. Combine lettuce and green onions. Add beef sauce and cheese. Sprinkle lightly with additional cheese.

title: marie's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as per directions; drain and return to cooking pan.
Add the butter or margarine; stir thoroughly.
In lightly buttered pan (either 9 x 13-inch or 9 x 9-inch), place 1/2 the macaroni.
Cover with 1 1/2 to 2 cups shredded cheese.
Add second layer of macaroni and cheese.
Beat the eggs with a fork or beater; add the milk, blending thoroughly.
Bake at 350° (325° if glass pan if used) for 40 to 45 minutes, or until cheese on top is slightly browned and a bit crusty.

title: pasta ala norcina
directions: In a frying pan, crumble sausage and
brown
in
margarine. Add wine.
When wine evaporates, add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook 15 to 20 minutes over medium
heat.
Cook
pasta according to directions.
Drain; add sauce and toss.

title: quick lunch box cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate and nuts, in a large mixer bowl; blend well at lowest speed of mixer.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown together beef and onion.
Add tomato juice, sugar, corn, beans and taco seasoning.
Cool all together.
Serve over corn chips.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Add spoonfuls of sour cream on top of cheese.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: In a shallow dish or pie plate, combine all ingredients, except pepperoni and olives.
Top mixture with pepperoni and olives.
