Bake at 325° about 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with rye chips, crackers of choice or assorted fresh vegetables. Yield: 36 appetizer servings.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill overnight.
Stir well before serving with corn chips.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble the cornbread and mix with the next 4 ingredients. Mix the mayonnaise and creamy cucumber dressing together; pour over the cornbread mixture.

title: sloppy joe potato topper
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef with peppers until beef is browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat. Stir in soup mix, water and ketchup.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon over potatoes.
Garnish with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam zucchini, onion and carrots 4 to 5 minutes. Then mix box of stuffing with melted butter. Stir in veggies, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and 1 cup of cheese. Top with other cup of cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Mash potatoes with milk and butter, but leave stiff.
Add pepper and onion.
Cool to room temperature.
Measure 1/3 cup portions; shape into cones.
Roll in bread crumbs, then in egg which has been beaten with water.
Place on greased cookie sheet; store in refrigerator.
Twenty minutes before serving, bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes, or until brown and crusty.

title: indian chicken curry
directions: In a small bowl, combine sliced apples and lemon juice; toss. Set aside.
Slice chicken; set aside.
Combine flour and chicken broth; stir until mixed.
Add all ingredients into skillet.
Cook on low for 30 minutes or until everything is cooked down; add extra water, if necessary.
Serve over rice.

title: easy breaded pork chops
directions: Spray cookie sheet.
Coat the side with mayo and then cover with the bread crumbs.
Coat top side only.

title: pineapple coconut ice cream
directions: Get milk hot.
Beat egg yolks, add sugar, flour and salt.
Mix into hot milk slowly, cook for a few minutes.
Cool.
Add pineapple, whipped cream, coconut, vanilla, beaten egg whites, 1 can of milk and lemon juice.
Put into freezer.
Add milk to fill. Very good.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften butter.
Blend with Ricotta until creamy.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add sugar gradually, beating until well blended.
Add egg and mix well.
Slowly stir in dry ingredients and blend well.
Drop from a teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Yields 30 to 36 cookies.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Roll pie crust.
Line pan; prick shell on bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce heat to 375°.

title: light okra or squash
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam cooking spray.
Roll okra or squash in meal, place on sheet.
Spray top of vegetable with cooking oil.
Salt.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until tender and brown.

title: tub salad
directions: Mix all together and put in a dish, 9 x 12. Freeze. Let thaw about 15 minutes before eating.

title: sweet potato fries
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into 1/4 inch by 1/2 inch strips. In a bowl, combine egg white and seasonings; beat well. Add potatoes; toss to coat. Place in a single layer on two baking sheets coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 8 servings. One 1/2 c. serving equals 40 calories, 20 mg sodium, 0 cholesterol, 9 gm carbohydrate, 1 gm protein, trace fat. Diabetic Exchange: 1/2 starch.

title: sour cream candy
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to a hard ball.
Add vanilla and beat with spoon.
Add pecans.
Drop quickly on waxed paper.

title: granny b's apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 4 (7 3/4 x 3 3/4 x 2-inch) loaf pans or 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch) loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350° for small pans or 375° for large pans.
Pare and slice apples.
Cover with water and set aside.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Bake the pie shell in a 425° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool while preparing filling.
Lower heat to 325°.
Cream the margarine with the sugar.
Beat in the egg yolks, rind, juices, flour and milk.
Beat the egg whites to soft peaks and fold into the lemon mixture.
Pour into the partially baked shell and bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until top is firm and golden.
(Good served warm.)

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Add sugar, cornstarch and salt to egg yolks.
Pour scalded milk into this.
Return to double boiler.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add the butter, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into a pie pan lined with pastry.
Bake.
Top with meringue.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Makes a 9 x 13 pan, thin layer, or double use the next size pan or have it thicker. Takes about 15 minutes to mix and bake for 1 hour.

title: vermicelli mushroom sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, heat oil.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saut until tender; add mushrooms.
Saut 2 minutes; add tomato sauce and seasoning; heat to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: herbed cheese and onion bread
directions: In a small bowl, proof yeast in 1/4 cup chicken broth for 10 minutes.
Into a large bowl, sift together the whole wheat flour and salt.
Add cheese, onion, rosemary, dill and marjoram and toss.
In another bowl, combine milk, the yeast mixture, chicken stock or broth, 1 egg and honey; when well combined, add to flour mixture, stirring until the dough is well blended.
Gradually add all-purpose flour and blend the dough until it forms a ball.
Turn the dough out onto a floured surface and knead it, adding more flour if it is too sticky, for 10 minutes, or until it is smooth and elastic.
Form the dough into a ball; put it in a buttered bowl and turn it to coat it with the butter.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine in blender or processor until smooth and slightly thickened.
Makes 14 oz.
(Same amount as can of Eagle Brand milk.)

title: chili mac
directions: In a large skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender. (Electric skillet at 350°.) Drain off fat. Stir in tomatoes, beans, tomato sauce, water, chili powder, salt and bay leaf. Bring to a boil, then add macaroni. Cover and reduce heat to low (220°). Simmer, stirring frequently, until macaroni is cooked (about 10 to 15 minutes). Remove the bay leaf before serving. Serves 6.

title: turkey-green grape salad
directions: Combine turkey, celery, grapes and mayonnaise. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Toss lightly. Serve on greens and trim with small bunch of grapes. Or serve in avocado halves brushed with lemon juice. Makes 6 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and cut cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Add green onions and radishes.
Mix garlic and cheese dressing according to package directions, then add mayonnaise, sour cream and caraway to it.
Blend well and pour over cauliflower and mix together.

title: cranberry banana christmas bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray a loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: cocoa-nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. In large bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan. Wrap tightly in foil.
Cool completely.

title: crabmeat muffins appetizer
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Spread mixture on muffin halves. Place under broiler until lightly toasted.
Makes 12 large portions.
Can be halved to make 24 portions or quartered for bite-sized portions.

title: three layer jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip until smooth.
Spread on pretzel layer.
Heat pineapple juice.
Add gelatin and strawberries (still frozen).
When thickened, pour on top of second layer.
Chill. When firm, serve in pan.

title: queen's favorite cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an average size dish (approximately 9 x 12 inches).
Add milk to flour and sugar.
Mix these three ingredients thoroughly and add to melted margarine.
Add peaches and do not stir.
Bake at 375° for approximately 40 minutes or until browning is noted.
This is excellent served while warm. For extra flavor, top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: oven-baked stew
directions: Preheat oven to 425.
In 2 1/2 quart shallow casserole, toss beef with flour, then bake uncovered for 20 minutes, stirring halfway.
Reduce heat to 350.
Add carrots, tomatoes, and bay leaf.
Blend soup mix with red wine and combine with other ingredients.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender. Stir in mushrooms and bake covered an additional 10 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add 1 egg at a time. Sift dry ingredients and add, alternating with sour cream.
Grease pan with shortening, then flour.
Bake 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: white bbq sauce for chicken
directions: Melt oleo.
Combine
dry
ingredients
and add to oleo. Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Combine remaining ingredients and gradually stir into butter mixture.
Return to heat.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Enough for 2 chickens.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk together in bowl. Pour into crust.

title: tina's easy banana cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add 1 cup warm water (not boiling) and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar, mayonnaise and gelatine to cream cheese.
Add pineapple, nuts and marshmallows; mix well.
Put into 10 to 12 individual molds.

title: pumpkin mousse
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding and beat with whisk and let stand 5 minutes.
Add pumpkin, spices and 2 cups Cool Whip. Spoon into crust and chill 4 hours.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cook meat in a little oil with onion and pepper until meat is brown and done.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook 5 minutes.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Foil line 9 x 13-inch pan; this helps in cleanup.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour milk in bowl large enough for chicken to fit in; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients, except chicken, in large Ziploc.
Dip chicken in milk, then shake in bag.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Stir in eggs and sour cream. Knead briefly and shape into a ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Use a sharp knife to cut an "X" onto top or spoon into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until brown and knife comes out clean.

title: creamy delicious cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350° in a
medium-sized bowl, combine crushed graham crackers and the butter.
Using your fingers, press the crumb mixture into the bottom of a 9- or 10-inch springform pan, forming the crust.
In a large bowl, with an electric mixer on medium speed, beat the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg until smooth and creamy.
Add the remaining 3 eggs and the sour cream an beat until well combined.

Add the heavy cream and beat for 2 to 3 minutes, or until well blended. Pour over the crust and bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until firm. Turn off the oven and open the door for 1 minute allowing the temperature to drop. Close the door and allow the cake to sit in the oven for 15 minutes.
Remove the cake from the oven, cover with aluminum foil and chill for at least 6 hours, or overnight, before serving.

title: beef and vegetables chinese style
directions: Cut the steak into thin strips, 2 x 1/4 x 1/4-inch.
Cut the bamboo shoots into thin strips.
Slice the water chestnuts.
Cut the onion into 8ths.
Slice the celery and carrot diagonally.
Cut large mushrooms in half.
Mix together the ginger, sherry, sugar, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Heat the oil in a frying pan with the garlic.
Saute garlic until browned, then remove.
Cook the beef strips until they change color, stirring constantly.
Add the soy sauce mixture, stock, vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to the boil, stirring and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water 15 minutes.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger, orange juice and butter and pour over carrots.
Cook, stirring occasionally for about 8 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ginger-cinnamon fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine the yogurt, cream cheese, ginger and cinnamon until well blended. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Serve with fruit.
Yield: 3/4 cup.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine egg, buttermilk and butter, slowly stir into dry ingredients (pancake batter will be very thick).
For each pancake spoon about 1/4 cup batter into a very hot skillet with moderate oil.
Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges are brown.
Serve with syrup.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind all together and mix well and chill. (It freezes well.)

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Blend in bowl the flour, salt, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and sugar.
Stir in milk and chopped nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch pan.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: zucchini fritters(martian pancakes)
directions: In blender, add pieces of zucchini to the egg until all mixed. Add spices and pancake mix until mixture sufficiently thickened for pancake batter.
Drop spoonfuls into hot oil 1-inch deep in frying pan.
Turn once when brown.
Good to eat with syrup.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls.
Mash balls down lightly with fork on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until very lightly browned.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Make topping first.
Mix the box of frozen strawberries, 4 tablespoons sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until bubbly. Cool in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: plain sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda together.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and oleo together.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, beating after each addition, then add vanilla.
Add small amount of flour mixture, beating until smooth until all flour is used.
Roll into small balls and drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: About 8 dozen.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Bring cream and milk to a boil in a large pan. Mix rest of ingredients except cornstarch together and add to boiling mixture.
Mix with whisk.
Burns easy.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Serve over hot fettucine.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Heat water and butter; add vanilla and chocolate.
Add confectioners sugar; beat until of spreading consistency.

title: easy ground beef lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan; stir until crumbly and drain. Add spaghetti sauce, water and seasonings; mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, eggs and half the Parmesan cheese in bowl.
Layer 1 cup sauce, 3 uncooked noodles, 1 1/2 cups sauce and half the cheese mixture in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Repeat layers.

title: salsa
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients well.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Keeps well refrigerated.
Makes 3 cups.

title: champagne cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed for about 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and pudding.
Mix well.
Pour over cake.
Pour pineapple on top and then top with Cool Whip, nuts and garnish with cherries. Refrigerate.

title: french market soup
directions: Sort and wash 2 cups bean mix.
Place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Soak overnight.
Drain beans. Add 2 quarts water and next 3 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove ham hock from soup.
Remove meat from bone. Chop meat and return to soup.

title: parmesan chicken bake
directions: *To make this recipe lower in fat grams, I spray my pan with Pam and use fat-free bread crumbs, using no margarine at all.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in baking dish and put in 350° oven to melt.
Make batter of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
When mixed, pour over butter (do not stir).
Empty can of peaches (drained) on top of batter.
(Do not stir.)
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good with ice cream.

title: southern meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a casserole.

title: cider punch
directions: Boil all ingredients for 15 minutes.
Let stand for 12 hours and strain.
Serve hot.

title: tater tots appetizer(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Wrap 1/3 slice of cheese and 1/3 slice bacon around Tater Tot. Serve with toothpicks. Bake until done.

title: the ultimate oatmeal cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to margarine mixture and mix well. Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and milk.
Add to other mixture (except butter). Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until firm and browned.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit. Mix rest of ingredients and stir in fruit. Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together 1 cup sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Put more than 1/3 in bottom of pie shell.
Save rest to go on top.

title: caviar supreme
directions: Soften cheese. Add mayo. Blend in lemon juice, onion juice and Worcestershire on a tray. Form mixture into a flat circle 1-inch high. Press parsley into sides and spread caviar on top (in middle) around top edge. Spread onions, then eggs. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate. Serve with Melba rounds.

title: honey refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together; set aside. Work shortening until soft and smooth.
Gradually add sugar and mix again.
Stir in honey, unbeaten egg and nuts.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Divide dough in half and shape each half into a roll.
Wrap each roll in wax paper and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans and seasoning.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Break taco shells in half at fold.
Place shells, rounded side up, along the sides of casserole and top with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with reserved taco shells and bake 5 minutes longer.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes just before serving.
Pass sour cream and taco sauce.

title: miss elsie's coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add other ingredients and cook in double boiler until partly thickened.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake until thick.
Beat egg whites for meringue. Sprinkle coconut on top and brown.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine white flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in wheat flour.
Fold in bananas, vanilla and chocolate chips. Pour mixture into pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Makes 1 loaf.

title: boo boo's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked crust. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: randall house dressing
directions: Shake or stir all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add this along with Cheez Whiz and broccoli. Beat eggs and add to mixture.

title: french meat loaf
directions: Mix
ground beef, onions, crackers and	egg.
Place
in meat loaf pan.
Cook in oven at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Prepare sauce with celery soup and milk mixture.	Pour
mixture
over meat loaf. Cook meat loaf and sauce for
minutes or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cocktail sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage,
biscuit mix and grated cheese.
Shape into cocktail size meatballs.
Place in baking pan and bake at 300° until lightly
brown,
about
minutes or less.
These freeze well.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine all the ingredients except beets.
Heat to boiling, the
add the beets.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes; chill.

title: no cream broccoli soup(low calorie)
directions: In large soup pot, heat vegetable oil.
Add onions, garlic, salt, pepper and thyme.
Stir until onions are softened.
Add broth and water.
Bring to a boil and stir in potatoes.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are fork-tender.
Meanwhile, trim ends and tough stalks off broccoli.
Cut flowerets and stalks of broccoli into 1-inch pieces.
Add to pot and cook until broccoli is tender.
Puree soup in a blender (for creamy soup).
Return to pot and add lemon juice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine the cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk, peanut butter and Cool Whip with mixer.
Drizzle syrup in bottom of crusts.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Dribble syrup over top.
Freeze.

title: scotch shortbread(missionary)
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Work in butter until the dough is the consistency of short crust.
Sprinkle board with rice flour.
Turn dough onto a board and knead until smooth.
Cut into portions and shape into rounds.
This amount will make 4 small rounds.
Place on grease-proof paper in a baking tin.
Prick with a fork.
Put in oven at 350°.
When the cakes begin to color (from 20 to 30 minutes), lower the heat.
Allow to cool in the tin.

title: blueberry-banana fridge pie
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and add sugar and mix well. Stir in Cool Whip. Cut up bananas and line bottom of pie crust. Add cheese/Whip mixture over banana. Spread gently the blueberry pie filling over the cheese/Whip mixture. Serve with a dollop of Cool Whip. This is delicious!!

title: cavatappi with spinach, beans & asiago cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss well. Sprinkle with ground pepper.

title: crab delight
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup.
Add cream cheese and beat smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 5-cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: mary wilcox's cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each.
Add flour, milk and lemon flavoring. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven.
Now turn oven to 350° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Depending on your oven, you may need to bake less time.
Watch for the top of the cake to get golden brown, and a knife inserted into middle comes out clean.
Invert onto a plate and cool out of pan.
No icing needed.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon up into small pieces.
Chop up onion.
Brown 1 pound hamburger with bacon and onion.
Add pork and beans, molasses, catsup, and dry mustard.
Mix and pour into casserole or baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: batter bread
directions: Let yeast dissolve in water.
Add salt, sugar and oil.
Stir in 2 cups of flour.
Knead in 1 more cup of flour (will be soft dough).
Return to bowl; cover.
Let rise, about 1 hour.
Knead and shape into loaf.
Place in loaf pan and let rise until double. Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheddar baked orzo with pepperoni
directions: In saucepan, saute pepperoni and onion over medium heat while stirring for 3 to 4 minutes.
Reduce heat and add flour with whisk to form a roux.
Whisk in broth.
Simmer sauce 2 minutes while continually stirring.
Whisk in Cheddar cheese, stirring until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup, cool slightly and add gelatin.
Add all ingredients together and mix well by hand. Chill in mold.

title: peanut butter "n" banana bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl stir together flour, sugars, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl combine mashed bananas, milk, peanut butter, oil, vanilla and egg.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Stir in chocolate pieces. Pour batter into two greased 8 x 4 x 2 inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50-55 minutes or until wooden toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool thoroughly.
Wrap and store overnight before serving.
To serve, frost with peanut butter frosting.
If desired, top with crushed peanuts and miniature semi-sweet chocolate pieces.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook beef until brown.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix rice, tomatoes and soup.
Add meat to bottom of dish.
Add rice mixture to top of this.
Stir in just a little meat.
Add Cheddar cheese to top.
Microwave until cheese melts. Serve on lettuce, also with Doritos.

title: shrimp pasta
directions: Grate ginger or cut into fine strips.
Heat a large frying pan and add butter, 2 1/2 tablespoons ginger, the mustard seeds and cashews.
Saut for 2 minutes.
Add precooked pasta (use a kind with ridges), coconut and cilantro.
Saut over medium heat until hot.
Set aside; keep warm.
Heat a large frying pan and add oil and 1 1/2 tablespoons ginger.
Saut 30 seconds.
Add shrimp (use large precooked ones), scallions and lime juice.
Saut until hot.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over hot pasta and garnish with lime wedges and cilantro.

title: microwave chili
directions: *Can substitute 2 (8 ounce) cans of tomato sauce for the can of tomatoes.

title: taco salad
directions: Heat beans (and meat, if used) in saucepan.
Pour into large salad bowl.
Add chips, cheese, olives, lettuce and tomato.
Pour salad dressing over the top.
Toss just before serving.

title: peanut pattie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and peanuts and cook in saucepan until a few drops of mixture forms in a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Take off heat, add butter, vanilla and coloring.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or foil.
Let cool. Yield:
25 to 30 patties.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Mix cheese, crab and garlic. Place fingertip amount on each wonton. Seal with water. Fry lightly in oil until lightly browned. Can reheat. Bake at 350° for 5 min.
Makes about 50 wontons.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix with meat, onion and celery.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Will be thick.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, butter and 2 Tbsp. sugar; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Add onto crust.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: To prepare; Sprinkle bottom of casserole dish (8 x 8) with part of cracker crumbs. Layer asparagus, grated cheese, and roasted almonds, alternating each. After dish is filled pour 1 cup of milk on one side of dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: favorite pudding dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, mix margarine, flour and nuts together and spread in 9 X 13 pan.
Bake about 15 minutes. Cool completely.
In medium bowl, mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread onto cooled crust.
Prepare pudding with milk and spread onto creamed cheese mixture.
Top all with whipped topping.
Chill until serving.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into gallon container.
Finish filling up with milk.
Put in freezer and freeze.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Look rice, do not wash. Put in bottom of casserole dish. Cover with soup, making sure all rice is covered. Melt butter in pan and cut up onion.
Add hamburger and simmer until it is crumbly.
Pour over soup and rice. Cover and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp.
Combine first 7 ingredients.
Toss to mix.
Serve with dressing.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Break up bread into small pieces; let bread dry out slightly.
Add bread to milk mixture. Add raw meat and mix thoroughly.
Form small balls.
Cook vinegar, brown sugar, dry mustard, water and salt and pepper until melted and blended together.
Pour over balls which have been placed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until lightly browned; turn occasionally.
Save sauce; reheat in serving dish.
Serve with long toothpicks.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Dip in your favorite fruit.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill a few minutes.
Form into 2 balls; let set overnight, then chop another cup of pecans and roll or pat the pecans on the ball.

title: mini fruit cakes
directions: Mix well all the ingredients and spoon into mini cupcake pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruited rice pudding
directions: Heat milk to boiling over moderate heat. Quickly stir in vanilla pudding mix and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in cinnamon dissolved in vanilla, sugar, currants and pineapple or favorite preserves. Stir in cooked rice and blend. Chill. Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from broth.
Bone chicken.
While boning chicken, add rice to broth.
Cook until rice is almost done.
Add mixed vegetables and chicken.
Simmer until vegetables and rice are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: catfish stew
directions: Saute onions in margarine or oil.
Add fish, water, pepper seeds with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover pan and simmer until fish is tender and flaky.
Serve over rice.

title: georgia hash
directions: Cut up potatoes to fry.
Put in a hot skillet with 1/4-inch oil.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not allow to become crispy. While potatoes cook, cut up other vegetables (amounts to your desire).
Add to potatoes along with salt and pepper to taste. Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash the avocados in a medium-size glass or wooden bowl.
Add the lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Set aside. Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasonings in a bowl. Set aside.
To assemble the dish, spread the bean dip on a shallow serving platter, a glass pie plate or a casserole.
Top with the avocado mixture, then the sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with the chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover the whole top with shredded cheese.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with tortilla chips.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Brown hamburger; add onions, peppers, tomatoes and tomato sauce from mix.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Roll crust in oblong dish. Layer 1 package cheese and 1 layer of meat.
Add other package of cheese and sprinkle with can of cheese that is in mix.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients together, then add the beaten eggs and wine vinegar.
Blend well.

title: snickers bars
directions: Melt together chips and shortening in a double boiler or microwave.
Pour half into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool.
Melt caramels with butter and water.
Add nuts and pour over cooled chocolate mixture in pan.
Cool again.
Top with remaining melted chocolate mixture.
Keep refrigerated until serving time.

title: enchilada verde casserole
directions: Remove bones and skin from chicken and shred, this should yield about two to three cups of chicken meat.
Line bottom of casserole dish, baking dish or bread pan with tortillas, cover but only one tortilla thick.
Divide ingredients into three units.
Then layer chicken, cheese, seasonings, green chilies and sour cream.
Spread the sour cream around so it covers the layer, repeat until you have three layers.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until the top is lightly brown and it is bubbling.
Serve with green salad, salsa and bread of choice.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Combine flour, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in 3/4 cup butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine eggs, milk and yeast mixture; add to the flour mixture, stirring well (dough will be sticky).
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Punch dough down and divide in half.
Roll each half into a 12-inch circle on a floured surface; cut each circle into 12 wedges.
Roll up each wedge tightly, beginning at wide end.
Seal points and place rolls, point side down, on greased baking sheets.
Curve rolls into crescent shape.
Brush with melted butter.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for an hour.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
In saucepan, add the last 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and stir often.
When cool, refrigerate.
Best if made a day ahead of time.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes. Remove and cool on rack.
Fill and frost with Coconut-Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in baked pie shell.
Cook water, sugar, cornstarch, flavoring and as much red food coloring as you want, until thick.
Let cool.
Pour over strawberries in shell, then refrigerate and serve.

title: coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients and pour into greased 9x13 in. pan.
Combine pecans, sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter.
Cut thru with knife to swirl.
Bake 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Combine sugar and orange juice until smooth.
Pour over hot cake.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except ketchup.
Place in a metal baking pan; form into loaf.
Cover bottom of baking dish with ketchup (1/2-inch deep).
Place in preheated 350° oven, depending on your oven, and bake about 1 hour.
The ketchup and juices from the meat make a wonderful sauce to serve over meat loaf.

title: fig nut bar
directions: Mix as mentioned.
Take half the dough; pat into pan.
Spread filling over it.
Take small pieces of dough; pat over top.
Bake. Cool.
Cut in strips.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and 1 cup water in saucepan, mixing well. Cook 45 minutes.
Braise chops or ribs in sauce in usual manner.

title: spaghetti florentine(international cuisine:  italian)
directions: Prepare spaghetti; brown ground beef and drain.
Stir herb-spice mix, tomato paste and water together.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
In 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, layer half of the spaghetti sauce, cottage cheese, spinach and Mozzarella cheese; repeat layers.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Make ahead; assemble casserole.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: easy italian cream cake
directions: Mix and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° 25-30 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir 2 cups milk in gradually.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Blend in vanilla and, if desired, 1 tablespoon butter.

title: creamy chicken chowder
directions: In a 4-quart pan, combine milk, broth and soups.
Blend well. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well and cook over medium heat approximately 10 minutes. Stir occasionally to prevent scorching.
Add cheese just before serving. Stir until melted. Served with crescent rolls and salad, this makes a great easy to fix meal.

title: rice with green chilies and sour cream
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package (quick-cooking rice may be used).
Combine cooked rice with sour cream and season to taste with salt.
Arrange half the mixture in the bottom of a greased casserole.
Cut the 1/2 pound of Jack cheese into domino-sized pieces and wrap them in strips of green chili peppers.
Place these on top of the rice in the casserole, add the remaining rice mixture, and dot with butter.
Cover with the grated Jack cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cafe au lait mix
directions: In an airtight container, combine all ingredients; mix well. Makes 2 cups of mix.

title: quick macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
In a 1 1/2 quart casserole, cook onion and butter in microwave on Medium-high for 1 to 2 minutes or until onions appear transparent.
Cube Velveeta cheese and cut up tomatoes.
Add all ingredients to casserole with onions.
Stir to mix.
Microwave on Medium-high heat for 2 to 3 minute intervals (stir in between) until cheese is melted.
Serve with Italian bread.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; stir well.
Add water and cook until clear.
Remove from heat; add jello.
Let cool.
Pour half of jello mixture into crust.
Add berries which have been cut into fourths; then add remaining jello mixture.
Top with 1 small container whipped topping.
Refrigerate until served.

title: baked steak
directions: Place steak in baking dish; season with salt and pepper. Spread with butter and add a layer of lemon.
Cover with chopped green pepper, top all this with chili sauce.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box using two 8-inch layer pans.
Split both layers horizontally after they have cooled. Blend together the sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Chill.
Spread all but 1 cup of the sour cream mixture between the layers.
Blend the remaining cup of the mixture with whipped cream.
Spread on top and sides of the cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Keep refrigerated after cutting.
(Ours never last the 3 day waiting period!)

title: ham pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a casserole dish. Top with the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.

title: helen's holly taters
directions: Cut potatoes (with skin on) into wedges.
Combine all other ingredients.
Drop and roll potatoes thoroughly.
Place on large flat pan.
Dab with 1 stick margarine.
Bake at 400° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: pineapple marlow
directions: Steam marshmallows over hot water and add pineapple.
Combine with whipped cream.
Pour into a greased tray to become firm. Does not require freezing.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbling; stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: two-cheese sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place in pan, not touching each other.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients to blend.
Put in casserole or six individual dishes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: crazy cheese straws
directions: Let the frozen puff pastry thaw (this takes about thirty minutes).
Preheat the oven to 400°.
Dust your countertop with flour.
Lay the puff pastry on the floured area.

title: broccoli tuna roll-ups
directions: Combine soup and milk; set aside.
Combine tuna fish, broccoli, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French onions.
Stir in 3/4 cup soup mixture.
Divide tuna mixture evenly between the tortillas and roll up; place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir tomato into remaining soup; pour over top of tortillas.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top center of tortillas with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and pecans; spoon batter into a greased 13 x
9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes or until top is barely soft to the touch.
Remove from oven and cover top with marshmallows.
Return to oven for 2 minutes or until marshmallows are soft.
Spread marshmallows over cake and immediately cover with frosting.
Let frosting harden before cutting the cake.

title: lemon jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until thickened.
Beat with blender and add defrosted lemonade, Cool Whip and orange marmalade.
Pour into greased mold pan and chill until set.

title: florida celery and eggplant croquettes
directions: Dice eggplant and onion.
Combine eggplant and onion with celery, salt and pepper.
Bring 1-inch water to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Add vegetables and cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Drain off water.

title: savory minestrone main dish soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown bacon and cook onion and celery with garlic and basil until tender.
Stir in soups, water, tomatoes, ditalini and salt.
Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and zucchini; cook 10 minutes more or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 8 cups.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain the artichoke hearts and marinated artichoke hearts. Cut them in small pieces and place in the bottom of a pie plate, quiche dish or serving dish or your choice.
Add the chopped jalapeno chili peppers and blend together.
Scoop out 4 to 6 tablespoons of mayonnaise on the top of this mixture and spread over the top.
Put the shredded cheese on top of the mayonnaise layer.
Heat in the microwave oven until the cheese melts or in a conventional oven at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with taco chips or raw vegetables.
This is a very popular appetizer.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and water with Kool-Aid.
Add ginger ale, pineapple juice and ice just before serving.
Freeze ice cubes with cherry.
Makes a pretty punch.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and remaining ingredients.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Chill dough overnight. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Do not pare cucumbers; slice thin.
Add onions, green peppers and sliced garlic.
Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice; mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to a boil. Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Use paper cups or grease a 12-cup muffin tin.
Mix dry ingredients, including nuts.
Mix wet ingredients.
Fold wet ingredients into dry.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as per package.
Brown beef and salt, pepper and garlic to taste; drain.
In a baking dish spoon a little sauce on bottom, then add noodles to cover bottom of dish.
Add Provolone cheese, Ricotta cheese and ground beef.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peach dessert
directions: Bake in tube pan at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fluffy cranberry cheese pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine gelatin and sugar; set aside.
In a saucepan, bring cranberry juice to a boil.
Remove from the heat and pour onto gelatin mixture, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in the cranberry sauce.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: ham rolls with orange rice
directions: Bring orange juice to a boil.
Lower heat and add rice.
Cook, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Combine chopped oranges with rice and mix with mayonnaise, pecans, parsley and onions.
Spoon mixture onto ham slices and roll as tightly as possible.
Place in greased baking dishes, seam side down.

title: drop egg in bowl chocolate cake
directions: Drop egg in bowl.
Cover with ingredients as listed.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese candy mints
directions: Mash and cream the cream cheese; add the powdered sugar gradually, stirring until the mixture becomes like a stiff dough. Add desired flavoring and food coloring, mixing ingredients thoroughly.
Roll in small balls and dip in the granulated sugar. Dip your mold in granulated sugar and press the ball down in the mold.
Unmold at once on waxed paper.

title: gina's orange whole wheat pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and oil together. Sift flour and baking soda together. Add to egg mixture. Gradually add orange juice until you have a good consistency. Add nuts to batter if desired. Fry on a medium hot griddle. Serve immediately.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add carrots and onion.
Saute vegetables 8 minutes.
Remove vegetables from skillet, reserving pan drippings.
Set vegetables aside.

title: hot artichoke cheese dip
directions: Squeeze artichoke hearts dry.
(I usually rinse them off with tap water after I drain the can.)
Cut up into bite size pieces. Combine with cheese, mayonnaise and garlic powder.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into loaf.
Bake at 400° to 450° about 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Allow about 1 1/2 hours to make and cook.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients according to directions on back of pudding mix.
Pour into molds, ice trays or small paper cups.
Insert popsicle sticks.
Freeze.
Makes 10 to 12 fudgsicles.

title: spinach salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first six ingredients in tight-fitting jar.
Shake to blend.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dressing.

title: tropic sun spareribs
directions: Rub ribs with garlic. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange onion in large baking pan. Place ribs on top.
Add 1/4 cup water to pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over ribs. Bake, uncovered 1 hour longer.
Serves 4.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Let set before serving.

title: meat balls
directions: In mixing bowl, put 1 mushroom soup, celery soup, eggs and medium handful of dried onions.
Stir with large spoon until completely mixed.
Open spice packet from stuffing mix and sprinkle 1/2 the packet evenly across mixture.
Stir in, then sprinkle remaining 1/2 packet and stir in completely.
Open can of mushrooms.
Using cover, squeeze off juice and discard.
Chop mushrooms into small pieces and add to mixture.
Remove bag of croutons and flatten with rolling pin into Grape-Nuts size pieces. Be careful not to powder croutons too much.
In a large bowl, put ground meat and chop until broken up.
Add mixture to meat.
With a large Baggie on hands, completely mix.
Make 2 to 2 1/2-inch meat balls and put in pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Spoon remaining mushroom soup over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: swirl coffee cake
directions: In large bowl, beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add the 1 cup sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add the eggs, vanilla and sour cream; beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Gradually add this mixture to the creamed mixture, beating at low speed just until blended.
Pour 1/2 batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon cinnamon and the chopped nuts.
Pour 1/2 of this sugar mixture over the batter.
Top with remaining batter and remaining sugar mixture.
Swirl lightly with knife to marble.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 375° preheated oven.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn out of pan to cool on rack.
Makes 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill on wax paper.
Shape mixture into log 8 x 1 1/2-inch.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: perfect pumpkin or sweet potato pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, spice and salt in a large bowl. Stir in pumpkin (sweet potato), milk and eggs.
Pour half of the mixture into each pastry shell.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until tests done.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: one bowl applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure all ingredients into large bowl. Blend 30 seconds on low speed, then beat 3 minutes on medium speed; scrape bowl often.
Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake 50 minutes for layer pans, 60 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan or 70 minutes for tube pan.
Test for doneness.

title: chocolate biscuit bread pudding
directions: Combine half and half and butter in a heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Cool.
Combine eggs, sugar and cocoa; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 1 minute. Gradually stir in half and half mixture; set aside.
Crumble biscuits into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Add egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean, covering with aluminum foil after 35 minutes to prevent overbrowning.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet potato fluffy
directions: Beat potatoes, butter, sugar, eggs, milk and orange juice until fluffy.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Pour in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candied yam boats - sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes with a brush.
Bake at 325° until tender, about 1 hour.
Remove the potatoes from oven. Cut in half lengthwise. Scoop out center of halves, leaving about 1/2-inch shell.
Set shells aside.

title: olive craver's kraut drop dumplings
directions: Cook kraut.
Be sure there is enough water to cover dumplings. Salt to taste.
Drop by spoonful into hot kraut.
Cook until done.

title: pot roast norway
directions: Roll meat in flour; brown slowly on all sides in little hot fat.
Mix and add remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook slowly 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: triple-cranberry sauce
directions: Combine cranberry juice concentrate and sugar in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil over high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add fresh and dried cranberries and cook until dried berries begin to soften and fresh berries begin to pop, stirring often, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in orange marmalade, orange juice, orange peel and allspice.
Cool completely.
Cover; chill until cold, about 2 hours.
(Can be made 3 days ahead.
Keep refrigerated.)

title: salt water taffy
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add water and honey.
Cook to 270°. Pull.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Use a heavy pot.
Saute garlic, celery, green onions and sweet onion in butter.
Add chopped potatoes, mushrooms and carrots; cook 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Whisk in 1/2 pint of half and half.
Serve hot with a little grated sharp Cheddar cheese and chopped green onion sprinkled on top.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar, and salt in pan.
Mix egg yolks and milk and add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Cook on medium heat until thicken, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie crust and top with meringue.
Bake at 350 for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add garlic and cook until yellow. Add soy sauce, salt, 1/4 cup water and cook for 45 minutes.
Add vegetables. Cook 10 minutes. Stir in cornstarch blend with 1 cup water. Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: grilled corn with garlic butter
directions: Stir together soft butter and minced garlic.
Cover mixture and chill.
Remove husks from corn, grill corn uncovered on a lightly greased grill rack over medium heat, about 10 minutes or until corn is tender.
Turn several times as needed.
Serve with garlic butter and salt while corn is still warm.
6 servings.

title: zucchini apple butter
directions: Cook Zucchini in small amount of water.
When soft, put through a blender.
Add sugar, vinegar, spices, and lemon juice to zucchini.
Put in a heavy saucepan and bring to boil on low heat until thicken.
Add Hot Candies until melted.
continue cooking until thickened, stirring constantly.
Put into hot jar and seal.

title: chinese meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into bite-sized balls.
Brown in hot oil before baking 30 minutes on broiler rack in 325° oven. Pour 16 ounces barbecue sauce over meatballs before serving. Reheat in 200° oven and add more barbecue sauce.
Serve from chafing dish.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Combine cake mix, applesauce, eggs and cocoa.
Beat 2 minutes. Fold in raisins and nuts.
Turn into a well-greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 9x12 cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's plain cake
directions: Soften shortening in a large bowl.
Beat in sugar until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in separate bowl.
Add half of flour mixture and half of milk to egg mixture and beat 300 strokes.
Add rest of flour mixture and milk; beat 300 strokes more.
Fill greased baking pan half full or pans.
Bake at 375° (moderate oven) 25 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
This is an old recipe and is good with strawberries over it.

title: sausage - chuck casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Pat sausage in casserole.
Brown meat.
Put in casserole.
Lightly brown peppers, onions, garlic and potatoes.
Add to casserole.
Put in spices; lightly toss.
Add beef broth; cover.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Layer broccoli in dish.
Mix soup, beaten eggs, cheese, onion, salt and pepper and pour over broccoli.
Melt margarine.
Crush cheese nips and sprinkle over broccoli casserole.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jane's whipping cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and whipping cream, a small amount at a time, on low speed of mixer.
Add flavorings.
Start in a cold oven set at 325°.
Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes, then turn out of pan.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan and press down.
Bake at 350°. Watch closely until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Let cool.

title: special k cookies(or rice krispie cookies)
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to rolling boil (one you can't stir down).
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add cereal.
Mix well and spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt margarine, sugar, milk, cocoa and vanilla.
Bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and boil hard.
Add oats.
Mix well and drop onto wax paper by the spoonfuls.
Let harden.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine milk, sugar, vinegar, egg, butter, cornstarch, salt, celery seed and mustard.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add onions and salad dressing. Peel and chop potatoes and hard-boiled eggs.
Fold in dressing. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: frosty strawberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Freeze firm.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook peas and onions together; set aside.
Cook carrots and celery together; set aside.
Cut up chicken; set aside.
In large pot, melt butter.
Add heaping 1/2 cup flour and blend well.
Add milk and cream and 2 cups chicken broth slowly.
Cook until sauce is creamy.
Add mixture to vegetables, chicken and lemon juice. Mix well and season to taste.
Pour into pastry lined 3-quart casserole.
Top with crust.
Slit top and bake at 350° to 400° or until browned.

title: smooth 'n creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in a small bowl; beat slowly with a rotary beater or at lowest speed of an electric mixer until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping and spread on cake at once.
Makes about 4 cups, enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.
Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir constantly until soft ball stage sugar, milk and butter. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 cups peanut butter.
Mix. Put in buttered pan.
Cool until hard.

title: aunt pearl's blackberry jam cake
directions: Sift together flour, cloves, allspice and cinnamon.
Add apples, dates and nuts.
Stir, coating fruit with flour mixture. Set aside.
Blend butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Set aside.
Dissolve baking powder in milk. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add flour mixture, milk, buttermilk and jam alternately to egg mixture.
Beat two minutes.
Pour batter into 4 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool and ice with date frosting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix with electric mixer to the Jell-O mixture the cranberry sauce.
Lightly grease an 8 x 12-inch dish or 10 x 10-inch glass dish or a large bowl.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in dish; let set in refrigerator. Spread the sour cream over the set mixture.
Sprinkle the chopped pecans over the sour cream.
Carefully pour remaining Jell-O mixture over pecans; let set in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, celery, onions and almonds together.
Fold in chicken, cooked rice and boiled eggs. Refrigerate overnight.
Cook covered at 300° for 30 minutes. Remove lid and add onion rings and cook for 15 minutes.

title: quick-as-wick hot dish
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of greased baking dish.
Crumble hamburger over the potatoes.
Add vegetable beef soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: easy chow chow
directions: Chop tomatoes and drain off juice.
Chop rest of ingredients and mix all of them together along with vinegar, sugar and salt. Add enough water to cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar. Add and mix the eggs and chocolate syrup. Combine in a bowl the flour, salt and baking powder. Gradually add to the chocolate mixture. Add the vanilla and nuts. Pour brownies into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spanish steak
directions: Melt butter in heavy frying pan.
Add onions and cook several minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on top of stove for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Scald but do not boil.
Can hot.

title: corn chowder(serves 4)
directions: Preheat large saucepan over medium heat about 1 minute.
Spray twice with cooking spray.
Saute the onions until translucent. Add 4 cups of the corn (2 cans) and saute 4 to 5 minutes, until softens a bit.
Add 2 cups chicken stock and cook until corn can be mashed easily.
Transfer contents of pan to a blender and puree until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Add pepper, rosemary, thyme, black pepper, cayenne pepper, 1 cup chicken stock and 2 cups corn (1 can).
Stir and cook 10 minutes more until it thickens. Garnish with the fresh basil.

title: individual or little cheesecakes
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixer for 5 minutes.
Place a vanilla wafer on bottom of a foil baking cup (midget size, 2-inch diameter).
Spoon a tablespoon of cheese mixture on top of each wafer.
Bake in a 375° oven for approximately 15 minutes.
Top with cherry, pineapple, strawberry or blueberry pie filling. Makes about 40 little cheesecakes.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Wrap each 1/4 apple in roll.
Place in casserole bowl.
Boil sugar, orange juice and butter together.
Add vanilla and pour over apples.
Bake 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
When baked spoon some juice over bread to glaze.

title: graham cracker yankee
directions: Place whole graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Boil sugar, egg, cream, butter and flour.
Remove from heat. Stir in crushed graham crackers, coconut and vanilla.
Spread over whole graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with another layer of whole graham crackers.
Frost with powdered sugar, egg and vanilla mixture.

title: pauline's ambrosia salad
directions: Alternate layers of bananas, oranges, pineapple, grapes and coconut in a bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Chill.
Add maraschino cherries just before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: olive-nut spread
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Use for open-faced sandwiches for teas and ladies functions.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients.
Drop cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dorito chicken
directions: Crush Doritos and spread over the bottom of a 2 quart glass pan.
Mix chicken, sour cream, chili powder, salt, garlic powder, and white pepper and place on Doritos.
Crush more Doritos on top and add cheese on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and nutmeg until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bananas and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Beat into creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: overnight salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges, reserving juices.
Place juices in a saucepan with lemon juice and water; stir in pudding mix. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill overnight.
Just before serving, fold in banana.

title: bean dip
directions: Put small amount of oil in frying pan. Smash beans and cumin together and simmer until well blended.
Put in 9-inch pie pan. Layer picante sauce, then cheese. Top with lettuce, tomato and onion. Dip with tortilla chips.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, saving drippings.
Remove bacon from pan.
Crumble and set aside.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Combine with beans, brown sugar, mustard, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour together.
Add eggs.
Mix well adding vanilla last.
Place rhubarb in pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over rhubarb.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Drain fruit.
Blend Cool Whip and pudding.
Fold in drained fruit and marshmallows.

title: chicken yum yum
directions: Melt margarine in medium-size roaster.
Season chicken with salt and pepper to taste (black or red pepper).
Add to cut up fryer.
Place in margarine.
Add the soup mix.
Stir around.
Add 2 1/4 cups water.
Wash rice and add to mixture.
Cover with lid and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Knead and roll out (about 1/2-inch thick) on floured board. Cut biscuits, butter tops and place one on top of the other.
Let rise 30 minutes and bake at 450° for about 12 minutes.

title: no bake soda cracker cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cracker crumbs and coconut; set aside.
In a pan, bring to a boil the white sugar and milk.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter; mix well.
Pour over cracker mixture; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let stand.
Nuts may be added, if desired.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in water until soft.
Mix all ingredients except sugar and potatoes.
Mash potatoes and sugar together.
Add to flour mixture.
Roll on floured board and cut into biscuits. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: In large skillet, cook onion in hot oil.
Add meat and garlic; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf and serve over hot spaghetti.

title: soap making - soft lye soap
directions: Soap Making:
To clarify fat, melt and add a few slices raw potatoes, letting them get a golden brown and the grease to bubble.
When this is done, strain through a cloth into a jar or lard pail.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Thinly slice steak across grain into bite size strips. Combine flour and sour cream.
Stir in bouillon granules, 1/2 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Set aside.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in crock-pot.
Mix sour cream and flour. Add soup and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Cook for 6 hours on low heat.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain frozen chopped broccoli.
In skillet, melt oleo and saute onion.
Add mushroom soup and garlic cheese and melt. Add cooked broccoli and mix.
Place in casserole and spread with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
It will keep several weeks.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Put in crock-pot. Add cheeses, olives and chiles.
Put on low until everything is melted.

title: mocha brownie cake
directions: Combine butter, 1 cup sugar and coffee until light.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in syrup until well blended; combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold flour mixture into batter until blended. Stir in 1 cup nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Combine remaining sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until sides pull away from pan.
Garnish with whipped cream, orange slices, nuts and mint leaves.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise with milk.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly with dressing.
Chill.

title: neens banana nut bread(makes 2 large loaves)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mash bananas.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time, in order.
Mix well.
Spoon into 2 large greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Remove from pan and let cool slightly.
Put in Ziploc bag until outer crust is moist.

title: german sausage scramble
directions: Brown sausage lightly in heated skillet.
Remove excess fat and reduce heat to medium.
Add onion.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, seasonings and sour cream.
Stir until potatoes are brown.
Add more sour cream, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Serve over Chinese noodles.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Combine flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Roll teaspoonful of dough into balls.
Place with sugar side up on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly brown and crinkly.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: boiled custard
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks and sugar. Beat egg whites and add gradually to yolk and sugar mix.
Beat thoroughly. Add about 3 cups of milk to mixture. Beat. Add to hot milk.
Cook and stir until foam disappears or mixture thickens (this will take quite a while). Add flavoring after removing from heat.
Refrigerate.
Recipe may be halved.

title: michigan blueberry pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 2 cups of the blueberries with sugars, flour, butter, lemon juice, nutmeg and salt.
Over low heat, cook mixture, stirring until it comes to boil and is thickened.
Cool and stir in remaining berries.
Turn filling into prepared pie crust and top with whipped cream flavored with 1 tablespoon sugar and vanilla.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: joyce's apple cake
directions: Melt butter and add sugar and eggs.
Beat together.
Add flour and spices; mix well.
Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured large loaf pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or in 2 small loaf pans at 325° for 45 minutes.
Bake ahead and freeze.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Place shredded cabbage in casserole.
Mix flour and sugar. Combine with cream and pepper.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover cabbage with bacon slices (uncooked).
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350° in covered dish.
Remove cover for a few minutes to crisp.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: In saucepan, saute onion flakes and basil in olive oil.
Add tomato sauce or paste; stir well.
Add salt, tomatoes and water; stir well.
Cook for about 1 hour.

title: no bake pie
directions: Mix well.
Put in pie crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: cream cheese noodles
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, combine water, bouillon and spices.
Bring them to a boil.
Add mushrooms and boil 5 minutes. Add noodles to boiling stock and cook according to package directions plus 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain stock retaining 1 cup. Return noodles to pot and add cream cheese and margarine.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted, adding enough stock to keep everything damp to wet.
(Serve immediately.)

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, cream and peanuts together.
Cook for 1 hr over very low heat.
Stir occasionally to keep from scorching. Add vanilla and red food color (as desired).
Beat until creamy and spoon out on wax paper to form patties.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute butter, celery, green pepper and onion.
Put in casserole dish.
Pull meat from the bone.
Dice and place in casserole dish.
Then add rice and mushroom soup.
Mix altogether. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream the butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside. Mix milk and pudding.
Add creamed mixture to pudding.
Stir in a large tub of Cool Whip.
Crush 1/2 package of Oreos and sprinkle on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour pudding over Oreos.
Crush the other 1/2 package of Oreos and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: smoked beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in oven until heated through.
Serve warm or cold with crackers.

title: red cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers (remove seeds with spoon).
Cut into rings or strips.
Soak in 1 cup lime and 1 gallon water for 24 hours.
Drain and wash; soak in water for 3 hours.
Drain and mix 1 cup vinegar, 1 bottle red food coloring, 2 tablespoons alum and enough water to cover cucumbers.
Simmer for 2 hours; drain.
Bring to a boil 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups of water, 10 cups sugar, 8 cinnamon sticks and 1 pack red hots.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours.
Drain again and save liquid.
Bring liquid to boil and pour over cucumbers.
Leave for 24 hours.
Drain again and keep liquid.
Place cucumbers in jars.
Bring liquid to boil and pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Chop green onions and mix with softened cream cheese and sour cream.

title: one dish meal
directions: Layer hamburger in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place sliced potatoes around on top of hamburger.
Sprinkle vegetables over the potatoes.
Add mushroom soup plus 1 can water.
Add salt, pepper and onion salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Twenty minutes before 1 hour is up, add cheese to cover and let melt.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: In a separate bowl, mix soup, milk, sour cream and onion.

In greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer cooked potatoes first, then 1/2 cheese, then potatoes. Pour soup mixture over layers; top with the rest of the cheese, crunched up corn flakes and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until bubbling in the middle.

title: cow chip cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Feeds many cowpokes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cube angel food cake, enough to not quite fill the whole 9 x 13 pan. Set aside. Beat cream cheese, sour cream and Cool Whip until blended. Fold in cubed angel food cake. Spread evenly into the 9 x 13 pan. Add fruit filling on top. Top with nuts if desired. Refrigerate.

title: cracker cake
directions: Add crumbs, shortening, 1 cup sugar, and 3 egg yolks; beat together.
Alternate this with 1 cup milk.
Fold in 3 egg whites. Bake in layers.
Mix in saucepan milk, 1 cup sugar, 3 egg yolks and butter.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and spread over baked cake.

title: mock chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and celery.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to bubbling.
Serve over noodles. (If celery is omitted, add another onion.) Excellent served with carrots and Chinese style rice.

title: traditional "chex" party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat butter in large shallow roasting pan in oven until melted.
Remove; stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereals, nuts and pretzels.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Makes about 9 cups. Party mix may be frozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.
(Use toothpick test.)

title: flatbread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and shortening until fine like cornmeal.
Then add cold water and mix.
Take about a tablespoon of dough and roll out very thin on a well floured board.
Bake flatbread on top of an electric grill until crisp.
This is delicious.

title: mexican dip
directions: Chop chilies.
Mix with soup.
Melt cheese in double boiler or microwave.
Mix all together.
Serve warm with chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit the baking powder.

title: pear relish
directions: Use food grinder.
Peel pears; hard pears are good for this. Combine all ingredients and cook until pears are tender.
Seal in sterile jars.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour into buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Add topping and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: pineapple whip
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Dissolve gelatine in cold water; stir into pineapple mixture.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to thicken, then stir in whipped cream, cherries and nuts.

title: friend of a friend's chicken
directions: Combine canned soups and milk; put rice in bottom of greased casserole.
Spoon soup mixture over rice.

title: broccoli-cheddar soup(this will serve 6 to 8 people)
directions: Place stock, pureed onion, celery, garlic and broccoli together and boil.
Cook until the broccoli is tender.
Prepare roux (butter and flour) and cook for 10 minutes.
Add the roux gradually to the simmering stock.
Stir with a whip until it thickens.
Cook low for an additional 10 minutes.
This can be stopped at this point if you want.
Add the cream and Cheddar Cheese to the hot soup, a little at a time, until the cheese has melted in.
Add salt and pepper last.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice onions.
Cut peppers fine.
Mix with salt and put cracked ice in it.
Let stand in the refrigerator for 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place all ingredients except soda in heavy pan; bring to boil. Cook approximately 7 minutes (hard crack in cold water).
Remove from heat, stir in soda, pour immediately onto greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and juice together.
Stir in dry pudding, then stir in miniature marshmallows.
Chill.
Ready to serve.

title: sweet and sour amish dressing
directions: Blend in blender.
Put in jar with 1 clove garlic. Will keep indefinitely.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Add dry yeast to water; mix with buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening, then add the milk mixture.
Knead slightly and roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 450°.
Do not let stand to rise as other rolls.
May be kept in refrigerator several days in covered container.
Pinch off, cut and bake as needed.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk, salt and butter until it forms a soft ball when a little is dropped into a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla and beat.
Pour into a well buttered platter.

title: "sensibly delicious" chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt 1/2 of the chips with sugar, butter and applesauce in saucepan.
Take off heat.
Add egg whites.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Add rest of chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Only 6 grams of fat in each square.)

title: layered refried beans
directions: Put all ingredients in order into a large casserole.
Put second 1/2 of picante sauce before corn chips.
Put into refrigerator before serving.

title: melting dreams
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Blend in the margarine.
Use hands, if necessary, and mix until smooth.
Shape into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with a fork.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 20 minutes or until the edges are lightly browned.

title: della mae's chicken and dumplings
directions: Bring broth and soup mix to a boil.
Break biscuits into small pieces and drop into hot broth.
Cook until biscuit pieces are tender (about 10 minutes).
Add pepper.

title: breakfast in a biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Spray muffin pan with vegetable spray. Open one tin of biscuits and press each biscuit into one cup of the muffin tin.
In small skillet, spray vegetable spray. Beat eggs and add salt and pepper; scramble.
Place 1 Tbsp. scrambled eggs on each biscuit.
Divide cheese, ham and salsa evenly over eggs.
Open second tin of biscuits and press over top of salsa mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: Heat butter and add flour.
Make a medium brown roux.
Add onion and saute until done. Add remaining ingredients except green onions and parsley.
Let simmer 1 hour. Add water for desired consistency. Add green onions and parsley. Simmer 15 minutes, then serve.

title: batter fried fish
directions: Break egg into 1-quart bowl.
Beat slightly.
Add milk.
Stir. In separate container, combine cornmeal, baking powder and salt, then add to milk-egg mixture, while stirring.
Add 1 tablespoon oil.
Stir.
Add enough flour to form a thin batter (about 1 cup). Cut fish into approximate 2-inch squares.
Salt to taste.
Preheat oil in deep fryer.
Test by dropping 1-inch cube of bread into oil. Cube should brown to golden in few seconds.
Dip fish in flour, then into batter.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Don't overcook.
Fry only 3 or 4 pieces at a time.
Drain on paper towels.
Be ready to serve at once.

title: chicken  breast supreme
directions: For each serving, use a chicken breast.
Remove skin.
Dip chicken breast in the soup that has been diluted with milk.
