Press into the stuffing mix, to which you have added the onions and parsley flakes.
Place coated chicken in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water and cool.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Mix flour, soda, salt.
Beat in flour mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form and fold into batter.
Pour batter into three 9-inch layer pans that is lined on bottom with waxed paper.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed in center.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove and place on racks.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in 1/8 wedges and cook in boiling salted water for 8 minutes.
Put drained cabbage in greased baking dish.
Melt oleo in saucepan and blend in cornstarch.
Add milk, salt and pepper. Cook until mixture thickens.
Pour this white sauce over cabbage. Top with pepper rings and the cheese and cover top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and break up broccoli.
Toss in peanuts, bacon (fried and crumbed) and onion.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise and curry.
Right before serving, toss in dressing.

title: soup(simple, but great chicken soup)
directions: Cover chicken with water, boil and spoon off scum that will rise.
Cook 1 more hour.
Pull chicken from the bone.
Put back in broth with carrots, celery, onion and allspice.
Cook 1/2 hour. Remove allspice before eating.
Serves 4.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheeses and mix well with pimentos.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Mash potatoes well in egg and 1 cup
flour.
Drop
into broth by	tablespoonfuls	(chicken,
beef
and
pork
broth). Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
These are very good and quick.

title: fruit-stuffed pork loin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Open pork flat on work surface.
Season with salt and pepper; rub in next 2 ingredients.
Combine scallions, bread crumbs, fruit and 1/4 cup apple juice.
Spread over pork.
Roll and tie to secure.
Place in rack set in roasting pan; add juice to pan.
Roast 35 minutes.
Bring preserves and pan juices to a boil.
Pour over pork.
Roast 15 minutes or until thermometer reads 160°.
Yields 12 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put all ingredients together in mixing bowl and beat lightly. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be baked in 2 pans and stacked or in 1 long pan.

title: new west chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, ginger and salt.
Stir in chicken, grapes, celery, green onions and walnuts.
Cover; chill before serving.

title: steamed dilled carrots(serves 3)
directions: Bring 1 inch of water in a medium saucepan to a boil.
Place carrots in a steaming basket and set the basket in the pan. Sprinkle the dill over carrots.
Cover and steam until carrots are tender, about 10 minutes.
Place carrots in a bowl and toss with the vinegar and juice concentrate.

title: sesame chicken wings
directions: Remove tips of chicken wings; freeze for making soup.
Bend each wing at the joint; cut into 2 sections.
Combine sesame seed, bread crumbs, paprika and salt in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken pieces in cream, using a brush to coat completely; roll in crumb mixture.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour to set the crumb coating. Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in the oven while it preheats to moderate (375°).
Remove pan from oven when butter is melted. Add chicken; turn to coat all over.
Bake in preheated moderate oven for 40 minutes or until golden and tender.
Serve with bottled duck sauce.

title: nacho dip
directions: In a square pan, layer bottom with cream cheese. Next layer 1 jar of salsa. Next add Hormel chili. Spread evenly and top with shredded cheese. Place in oven until cheese is bubbly and toasty. Serve with nacho chips. It's quick and delicious!

title: thrifty punch
directions: Mix cherry drink with sugar and juices in a 6-quart punch bowl.
Add water and stir well.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.
Yields 25 servings.

title: ham and potatoes
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Layer ham, potatoes and onions.
Pour soup mixture over ham, potatoes and onion mixture.
Bake at 350° until potatoes and ham are done.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and stir well.
Store in refrigerator. Serve
over cream cheese as an appetizer or with pork or beef. This
sauce
is
great to make ahead of time because it keeps for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil sliced carrots until tender.
Cool and drain.
Layer in a non-metal bowl with sliced onion.
Heat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrots and onions.
Marinate overnight, stirring several times.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all together and roll out real thin.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut tortillas into strips.
Put chicken in large pot; cover with water.
Cook until done.
Save chicken broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix soups, cheese and tomatoes.
Dip tortilla strips into chicken broth and layer chicken, tortillas and sauce; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and corn flakes or potato chip crumbs.
Bake for an additional 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Make this the day or night before.
Serves 10.

title: sonny's favorite chicken dressing
directions: Boil hen in 3 quarts salted water until tender.
Remove from broth, set chicken aside and reserve broth.
Take corn meal and salt, add water until slightly soupy.
Generously grease iron skillet.
Add mixture and bake in 400° oven until light brown and crusty.
Add to broth and allow to sit awhile to absorb broth. Boil onions and celery in water with 2 tablespoons of margarine. Cook until onions and celery are clear and tender.
Add all to chicken broth, crumble crackers finely and add to broth mix.
Beat eggs until frothy and add slowly to broth mix to prevent quick cooking of eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Use potato masher to make mixture soft and slightly soupy (may add canned broth) and without lumps.
Grease well one large baking pan or 2 large casserole dishes.
Pour in mixture, then add corn oil to top for browning.
Cook in hot oven (approximately 400°) until brown, but soft in center.
Best served hot.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Place caramels, water and butter in double boiler. Heat until melted, stirring until smooth. Combine sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla. Mix well; add to caramel sauce and pecans. Stir well. Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 12 muffin cups or line them with paper baking cups. In a large bowl, cream the butter with the sugars and cinnamon until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs. In a small bowl, sift flour, baking soda and salt together. In a separate bowl, combine the coffee, milk and vanilla. Blend the liquid ingredients into the flour and butter mixture. Fill muffin tins and bake for about 25 to 35 minutes. Cool briefly on wire rack. Serve warm with butter. Makes 12 servings.

title: white flour pancakes
directions: Combine all dry ingredients - mix in all others.
Heat griddle until hot.
Drop pat of butter to grease pan.
Add 2 -3 Tblsp. Mix onto pan making shapes or circles.
Cook until golden brown and flip over once.
Makes approx. 12.

title: bavarian-style chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add Crisco, chocolate and 2/3 cup milk.
Blend for 30 seconds, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, rest of milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spread batter in long cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35
minutes.

title: rum pie
directions: Scald milk in double
boiler.
Add beaten egg yolks and 1/3 cup sugar.	Cook
over
boiling water until spoons coated. Remove from heat and add Knox gelatine;
stir until dissolved.

title: chicken spaghetti dinner
directions: Put chicken in Dutch oven; add salt and cover with water. Cook until tender; cool and remove from bone.
Add ingredients through salt and pepper; simmer 20 minutes.
Add boxes of cut spaghetti and cook until tender.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 of grated Mozzarella cheese; mix very lightly.
Add more water, if needed.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs well.
Mix cocoa, coloring and vinegar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Cook for 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: low-fat mac and cheese
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain.
In a large bowl, combine pasta with cheese, onion, pimentos, black and cayenne peppers, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spoon into a lightly oiled 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake in a preheated 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: white chili
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in kettle and cover with water.
Soak at least 24 hours.
Drain.
Cut chicken into pieces and put in a pot. Cover with at least 5 cups water.
Bring to a simmer and cook until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in margarine for 5 to 10 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream and cook on low heat for 10 minutes or until thick.
Be careful that mixture does not come to a boil.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually work in sugar until mixture is smooth and light.
Beat in egg yolks; sift cake flour over cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Toss with hands until fruit and nuts are well coated with flour.
Stir floured mixture into creamy mixture and add extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold them into batter thoroughly, but gently pour batter into well oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours or until done. Cool on wire rack about 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Cool cake completely before slicing.
Can be frozen.

title: debbie rogers baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and onions together. Mix with all other ingredients, then pour into crock-pot and cook all day on LOW heat.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Oil pizza pan lightly.
Cut dough in 1/8-inch slices.
Place in pizza pan to cover bottom of pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes; cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cookie crust.
Add fruit in order in circular arrangement.
Make glaze of preserves and water.
Dob glaze over fruit with spoon.
Chill until ready to serve; be sure to glaze the bananas!

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together; shape into balls (walnut size).
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip into melted chocolate.

title: poached fish
directions: Place all ingredients, except peppercorn and lapu-lapu into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and allow to simmer for 1 hour.
Add peppercorns and allow to simmer for 10 minutes more.
Pass through a food mill or a fine strainer.
Place clean and dry lapu-lapu or other white meat fish in tepid court bouillon and bring to a boil. Lower flame and allow to simmer until fish is cooked.
May be served with Hollandaise sauce or mock Hollandaise sauce.

title: tennessee pumpkin bread
directions: Grease a regular loaf pan or 4 small mini pans.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a medium bowl cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin. Stir in dry ingredients in 4 additions alternately with water (3 additions) just until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in nuts. Turn batter into prepared pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until cake tester comes out clean 45 to 55 minutes or 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn out on a wire rack, right side up.
Store, tightly covered.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain pork and beans, saving the liquid in a skillet.
Brown bacon, beef and onion.
Combine all three beans with browned meat. Combine all of the rest and pour beans and meat in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together pistachio pudding and crushed pineapple.
Add marshmallows, pecans and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: spiced oatmeal
directions: Bring 3 cups water to rapid boil; add oatmeal.
While oatmeal is cooking, add coconut.
Remove from burner and add butter and brown sugar.
Serve with hot buttered toast.
Serves 6.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix broken pieces of Hershey bars, chips, vanilla, marshmallow cream and margarine in a 6 to 8-quart pan.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and milk in a 4 to 6-quart pan.
Boil and cook for 6 1/2 minutes. Pour the cooked
sugar and milk over first mixture and blend.
Add chopped pecans.
Drop balls onto waxed paper.
Let stand for 4 to 6 hours, or until chilled.
Remove from paper and store.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: collard greens and turkey wings
directions: Soak and wash collard greens.
Remove all grit.
Remove hard stems.
Place greens together in small bunches.
Roll together. Cut crosswise into wide strips.
Place greens, water, onion and turkey wings in large pan.
Season with sugar, pepper, garlic and salt substitute seasoning.
Cook until greens are soft and tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix all of the ingredients together, except the bread.
Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours before serving. Hollow out the center of the bread and pour dip into it.
Break up hollowed-out bread for dipping.
Add raw vegetables, breadsticks and more bread for dipping.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Combine chili, cheese and chilies in a saucepan or fondue pot. Heat over medium-low, stirring frequently, until the cheese melts.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Yields 12 servings.

title: skillet beef noodles
directions: Brown beef in electric skillet.
Drain off any excess grease; add tomatoes, onion soup mix, salt, pepper, oregano, sugar and mustard.
Mix well and add uncooked noodles; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add whole kernel corn.
Stir and heat for 5 more minutes.

title: coffee swirl cake
directions: Grease tube pan. Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans together. Put 1/2 of nut mixture in pan. Mix cake mix, instant pudding, water and oil together. Add eggs 1 at a time. Beat well. Put 1/2 of cake mixture in pan. Add other 1/2 of nut mixture then add other 1/2 of cake mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar together with hands; add flour and mix some more.
Shape into balls and prick with a fork about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo gradually.
Add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add bananas and mix until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, stirring just enough to moisten.
Stir in chopped pecans and raisins.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350 degrees for one hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to completely cool.
Makes 1 large and 1 small loaf.
This freezes well.
(Good for muffins, too.)

title: california dip for vegetables or chips
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Flavor is better if made the day before using. Keeps up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Add other ingredients in order given. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Toss all ingredients and enjoy.

title: dietetic fruit cake
directions: Add oil to applesauce and egg. Add sweetener. Sift dry ingredients together. Add lemon and orange rinds. Add fruit and nuts to dry ingredients.
Add applesauce mixture.
Mix well. Cook in tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: soup burger skillet meal
directions: In a large skillet, brown chopped hamburger and drain. Add soup and beans and simmer until hot. Spoon onto buns as a sandwich or open face as a meal. Serves 4.

title: charlie's peanut brittle
directions: Butter 2 baking sheets, each 15 1/2 x 12 inches; keep warm. Combine soda, 1 teaspoon water and the vanilla; set aside.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put apples in pan with sugar, cinnamon and water; cook 10 minutes.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Pat on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Cook on medium heat in saucepan until bubbly thick.
Continue to cook and use mixer to smooth mixture.
Pour in cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue when cool.

title: nut cake
directions: Flour pecans and soak in one bottle of black walnut flavoring. Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add all other ingredients.
Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake date crunch bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan with butter or margarine.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Boil butter, sugar and dates together 5 minutes. Stir constantly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour over Rice Krispies in a large, buttered bowl.
Mix.
Spread in pan.
Dust with more powdered sugar.
Cut when cool.

title: lou's sherried chicken
directions: Bone breasts of chicken, leaving the skin on.
Cut breasts in half, making 6 pieces.
Form each piece into a ball with skin stretched over ball.
Arrange in baking dish.
Place in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, sherry and paprika.
Use the can to measure out a half can of sherry.
Blend well.
Add paprika until mixture is red.
Remove chicken from oven after 30 minutes.
Remove skin from chicken and drain off liquid.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Use all the mixture.
Return to oven for an additional 30 minutes.
Serve with rice and vegetables.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon sugar over pie.
Cover edges of crust with foil while baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans(microwave)
directions: Combine onion, green pepper and bacon in a 1-quart casserole. Microwave until done.
Drain off grease if you wish.
Add remaining ingredients and microwave on High until bubbly.

title: freezer sweet pickles
directions: Mix cucumber slices, onion and salt well and let stand 2 hours.
Drain; do not rinse.
Mix sugar with vinegar, stir well and pour over cucumber slices.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in ice cream freezer.
Fill 2 or 3 inches from the top of freezer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream or ice cream if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Prepare stuffing as directed on box. Layer chicken and stuffing mix in baking dish.
Cover with cream of chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for half hour or until heated through.

title: homemade pastrami
directions: Trim excess outside covering of fat from brisket.
Barely cover meat with cold water.
Add garlic, bay leaves and red peppers.
Cover pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook for 30 minutes to the pound or until meat is tender, but still firm.
Lift meat from liquid to shallow baking pan.
Brush both sides lightly with liquid smoke.
Pound or crush whole spices together in mortar until medium fine.
Pat onto both sides of meat.

title: corn bake
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in shortening.
Add corn, beaten eggs, and corn muffin mix.
Stir.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix sour cream and grated cheese and spoon over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Place raisins in pan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Take off heat and let cool.
Should be only a little water left in pan.
Keep it; do not drain.

title: marsala breast of chicken
directions: Mix. flour with pepper and paprika and lightly dust chicken breasts.
Melt butter in hot skillet.
Saute chicken gently over low heat until golden on both sides and juices run clear.
Remove to platter and keep warm in 200° oven.
Pour wine into skillet, scraping brown bits into wine.
Add mushrooms and cook until wine is reduced by 1/2.
Pour sauce over chicken and sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 2.

title: won ton
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Place a teaspoon of filling in the center of the wrappers, using a small amount of water to seal the edges.
Fold into triangle and then deep fry until golden brown.
Yield:
80 to 90 pieces.

title: chocolate cream cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line 18 muffin cups with paper liners.
In a small bowl combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.

title: creamy pesto pasta salad
directions: Mix pesto and salad dressing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter and stir in flour, salt and pepper to make a smooth paste.

title: dirty rice
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients (do not cook meat) in a large mixing bowl.
After mixing, pour into prepared baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: caramel-coconut pie
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet; add coconut and 1/2 cup pecans. Cook until golden, stirring frequently. Set aside and let cool slightly. Combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk; beat at medium until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Layer 1/4 of cream cheese mixture in each pie shell. Drizzle 1/4 of caramel topping over each pie. Sprinkle 1/4 coconut mixture evenly on each pie. (Repeat layers cream cheese, caramel and coconut.) Cover and freeze at least 8 hours. Let frozen pies stand at room temperature 5 minutes before serving. Makes 2 pies.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Cook onion in butter in a large saucepan over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes until tender.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook for 3 to 5 minutes, until no longer translucent in center.
Remove shrimp to a bowl with slotted spoon.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper to saucepan.
Simmer for 4 to 6 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and half and half.
Bring just to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Turn off heat; stir in cheese and parsley.
Let stand for 2 minutes until cheese melts. Stir in shrimp and serve.

title: baked beans(great for a barbecue!)
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet.
Drain grease and add seasonings.
Saute until wilted. Add mustard, ketchup and barbecue sauce; mix well.
Add beans and pour into casserole dish.
Lay bacon slices on top and bake at 325 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground meat with chopped onion.
Stir to separate meat particles.
Add soup, mustard, ketchup and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon onto 8 split, toasted buns.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into quarters.
Place in a large skillet with tight fitting lid.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place on stove and cook until tender with lid on to retain steam.
Turn cabbage a couple of times.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound boneless chicken very thin.
In one bowl, mix eggs and a little milk.
In another bowl, mix breadcrumbs, salt, pepper and seasonings.
Pour Wesson oil in frying pan and heat.
Dip chicken into egg mix and then breadcrumbs mix.
Cook in oil until chicken is done.
Layer in baking dish.
Top with spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg yellows.
Sift flour and soda together; beat together.
Add sour cream; add vanilla.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Let sit while preparing topping.

title: hot pepper pecans
directions: For each cup of large pecans, melt 2 tablespoons of butter in shallow pan.
Spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir several times.
Mix 2 teaspoons soy sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 3 or 4 dashes of Tabasco sauce into the toasted nuts.
Pack into jars with tight lids.
Will keep 4 to 5 weeks if tightly covered.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Place 3 whole unpeeled eggplants in the oven on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 450°.
Remove and peel; chop into cubes.
Place chopped eggplant in a large bowl.
Soak in a mixture of lemon juice, water and salt for 20 to 30 minutes.
Then, place the eggplant cubes into a blender with onion and salt and pepper to taste; blend well.
Place dip on a plate or low bowl and decorate with black olives and parsley.
(This is a great dip for vegetables.)

title: white bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Blend well.
Heat water and shortening (to 120° to 130°).
Add water mixture to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed, then medium speed for 3 minutes. Stir in remaining flour until soft and pliable.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover with clean cloth and let dough rise until doubled (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down dough, removing all air bubbles.
Divide in half.
Shape into 2 loaves. Place in greased bread loaf pans.
Rise until dough is 1-inch above edge of pan.

title: fruit cake
directions: The cherries and pineapple are candied fruits.

title: grandma's fudge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream together margarine, egg yolks and sugar. Add chocolate, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into two greased 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake slightly longer if using 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Frost with white icing.

title: brownies for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Stir by hand.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with nuts before baking.

title: english muffins
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water (110°).
Combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add yeast and mix.
Add enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth (8 to 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, turning once.

title: cream puffs
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in lukewarm water; add milk, shortening and salt.
Mix.
Stir in flour (it may be necessary to add a little more flour to make the dough more easy to knead). Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Put by tablespoons into ungreased muffin tins (do not fill over 1/2) or you can put in baking pans and have them connected together.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Brush tops with butter and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orpha snowden's quickie cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a pan and add fruit.
Mix thoroughly the flour, milk and sugar.
Pour over the fruit and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
I always add a little sugar to the fruit.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Place in a greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° until bread crumbs are browned.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Stir melted margarine and brown sugar together.
Add egg and vanilla to margarine mixture and stir.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir together.
Add chocolate chips. Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool before slicing.

title: chicken balls
directions: Cut up chicken in small chunks and fry.
In small mix cream cheese, butter, Lawrys, and garlic salt until the cream cheese is real soft. Add cooked chicken. Roll in crescent rolls. Bake about 20 minutes. Makes about 16 chicken balls.

title: cheesy broccoli cauliflower soup
directions: Combine the first six ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes until vegetables are tender. Meanwhile, in a saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour until smooth. Gradually stir in milk. Bring to a boil and stir for 2 minutes until thickened.

title: egg-stuffed zucchini
directions: Halve zucchini lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp to make 1 cup; set aside.
Place zucchini shells, cut side down, in large skillet.
Add the water and simmer, covered, until just tender (5 to 6 minutes).
Drain; turn cut side up in same skillet.
Sprinkle with a little salt. Meanwhile, in medium skillet cook zucchini pulp and tomato in butter until squash is tender (about 3 minutes).
Add eggs, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until just set, lifting with spatula so uncooked portion runs underneath.
Spoon egg mixture into zucchini shells.
Top with cheese.
Cover; heat until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican rice(serves 4)
directions: Bring chicken broth to boil.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil for 2 minutes.
Add rice; saute for 2 minutes.
Add boiling chicken broth, cumin and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add tomato and chives; simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir and set aside (covered) for 10 minutes before serving.

title: pierogi
directions: Mix together cheese, eggs, salt and onion.
Add flour until batter holds together.
Drop spoonfuls of batter into boiling water to which 1 tablespoon salt has been added.
Boil 3 minutes. Fry in butter and serve with sour cream.

title: stuffed burgers
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Combine milk and beef; divide into patties on waxed paper.
Pat into 6-inch circles.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each, draw meat over stuffing and seal.
Place in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix well. Roll in waxed paper.
Slice and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until slightly brown. Dust with 10x sugar, tops and bottoms.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Chop all ingredients very fine.
Mix with wine vinegar and add sugar.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Place 1 slice of onion in the bottom of each jar, then fill with sliced pickles. Pour hot liquid over pickles and seal.
Put jars in hot water and bring to a rolling boil.
Remove jars from water.
Fills 7 pints.

title: impossible pumpkin pielubbock, texas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 or 10-inch pie pan.

title: easy fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan over low, direct heat.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients to saucepan, mixing well.
Pour into well-buttered round 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into slices before pie cools.
Delicious served hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except the ginger ale.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Prepare pie pan by lining with bottom crust.
Break Ritz crackers coarsely into the unbaked crust.
In a saucepan, combine water, sugar and cream of tartar.
Boil gently for 15 minutes. Add lemon juice and rind.
Cook for about 10 minutes.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Generously dot with butter or margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.
No one will know there's not a lick of "apple" in your apple pie!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat to boiling, then simmer.
Stir occasionally.
It may thicken.

title: caesar salad
directions: Tear
the
romaine
lettuce
into
bite-size
pieces. Reserve.
Rub
salad
bowl
with
clove of garlic.
Into salad bowl, add the olive oil.
Crush the garlic into the olive oil. While
whisking
constantly, break the egg into the salad bowl mixture.
When
this
mixture
achieves
a smooth consistency, very
slowly add lemon juice, until it has a creamy look.
Add 1/2 of
the
cheese
and
mix
again.
At this point, add the chopped anchovy filets and 2 tablespoons wine vinegar.
Whisk this mixture
until
smooth.
Add lettuce, coating well.
Add remainder of cheese and top with croutons and artichoke hearts (drained). Serve on chilled plates.
Serve with London Broil.

title: italian meatballs
directions: By
hand,
mix	all
ingredients
very thoroughly.
The mixture is	right
and
ready
when the whole piece of meat is gathered in
the center of your bowl.
Mix and fold until this happens.
Form into meatballs the size you prefer.	Cook until brown
on
both
sides in hot oil.	Drop gently into spaghetti sauce.
Let meatballs cook in sauce for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: barbecued sauerkraut
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in skillet; drain off fat.
Drain 1/2 of the juice off kraut.
Combine onion and beef mixture, kraut, tomato sauce and brown sugar.
Turn into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Peel peaches and slice.
In a large bowl, toss peaches, 1/2 cup sugar, flour, lemon juice, salt and cinnamon.
Pour into glass casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover with tinfoil and bake in oven at 425° until hot and bubbly, about 35 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: *If using large package, use deep dish pie shell.

title: master cake mix
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar to blend.
Stir 3 times.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or electric mixer. Store in covered container at room temperature.

title: reduced calorie vegetable dip
directions: Mix contents of party dip with sour cream and milk. Mix gently with wire whip or spoon. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving. Perfect dip for chips, vegetables or crackers.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set; top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Chill. Serve with favorite topping.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: berry crisp
directions: Toss berries with sugar and flour (enogh to coat).
Place the berries in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Combine 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in egg.
Mix until well blended and crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of berries.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or milk.

title: hearty pancakes
directions: In bowl, combine flour, oat bran, sugar, baking powder, milk, Egg Beaters and margarine.
Using scant 1/4 cup for each pancake, portion batter onto lightly greased nonstick griddle or skillet. Cook over medium heat, turning once to brown both sides.
Serve topped with sliced strawberries if desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In
casserole
dish,
pour
2 cups rice.
Sprinkle with salt. Heat
soup
in saucepan with 1 can water.
Pour half on rice. Place
chicken pieces on top.
Pour remaining soup over chicken; sprinkle
with salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until fork-tender.

title: curried turkey salad with georgia peach chutney
directions: Combine turkey, onions, chestnuts, rice and raisins in a large bowl.
Prepare a sauce using remaining ingredients, except peanuts.
Fold sauce into turkey mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve on curly leaf lettuce and garnish with peanuts.

title: sausage
directions: Mix together and grind.
You can use less black pepper and more cayenne, if desired hotter.

title: window cleaner
directions: Put into a spray bottle.
Make sure window is totally dry or it will streak.

title: super simple potato salad
directions: In an ungreased 3-quart microwave-safe plastic bowl, combine frozen hash brown potatoes and water; spread evenly in bowl. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 20 minutes or until potatoes are hot and tender, stirring once halfway through cooking time.

title: cheeseless cheese cake
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Blend well and pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Fat free.

title: low calorie onion soup dip
directions: Blend yogurt and cottage cheese in medium bowl; stir in onion soup mix and chili powder.
Refrigerate, covered, for 3 hours. Place on tray with an assortment of crisp vegetables.
Yields 2 cups.

title: surprise salad
directions: Boil together first 3 ingredients.
Remove from fire and add cold water.
Refrigerate.
When almost congealed, fold in remaining ingredients.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Heat oil.
Dip chicken in flour mixture, then in egg and brown in oil.
Set chicken in baking pan and put a thin slice of lemon on each piece.
Mix 1/4 pound stick of margarine, 1 MBT packet, juice of 1/2 lemon and parsley flakes.
Pour mixture over chicken and freeze.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Spray with Pam. Arrange graham crackers with sides touching on cooking sheet.

title: cracker ice box cookies
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar, milk and egg. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add graham cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut. Line a 9x13 inch pan with whole graham crackers. Spread the cooked mixture over the crackers. Add another layer of graham crackers. Make frosting; mix confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla. Spread this over final layer of graham crackers. Chill in refrigerator about 3 hours before cutting. (A ready to spread frosting may be used.)

title: peanut butter fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and cream in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to a full rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares. Makes 3 pounds.

title: cajun eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients well and cook to desired wellness.

title: mam-maw mize's lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, flour, salt, lemon juice, butter and water.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into baked crust.
Top with meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except cracker crumbs and margarine.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is a good dish for covered dish dinners and can easily be doubled or tripled.

title: strawberry pie filling
directions: Cook until clear the sugar, water and cornstarch.
Remove from heat and add jello and some butter.
Let this filling cool.
Add berries to this.
Put in pie shell.
Put topping on top, such as Cool Whip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine ground cranberries and sugar and let stand overnight. Drain in mesh sieve and add grapes and chopped nuts.
An hour before serving, stir in whipped cream.

title: little drumsticks
directions: Marinate little drumsticks from chicken wings overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Do not cover.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients all together and put in greased baking dish (large dish).
Top with a layer of crushed corn flakes.
Melt oleo and pour over before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw dough and allow to reach room temperature.
Mix brown sugar and cream or milk.
Spread into bottoms of two greased (9-inch) round baking pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of nuts over the bottom of the pans.
Roll dough into 10 x 18-inch rectangle.
Spread with butter, leaving about 1/2-inch without butter on one 18-inch side.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over dough, then sprinkle remaining nuts over the sugar.
Roll up like a jelly roll, ending with the side that does not have butter on the edge.
Pinch to seal the edge.
Cut into 1-inch slices and put cut-side down into pans.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake or the caramel will harden.
Put waxed paper on wire racks and cool rolls with caramel side down.
Serve warm or cold. Makes 18 large rolls.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix all well.
Put into 16 paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 350°.

title: onion stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, cook onions in butter until soft and slightly golden in color, dividing into two batches, if necessary.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Let ice cream and Cool Whip get to room temperature; mix.
Add Oreos.
Pour in one or two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Freeze and cut into squares later.

title: canning jar bread
directions: Wash and dry
8 pint size wide mouth canning jars or 5 to 6 wide mouth pint and a half jars.
Grease well.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and water.
Beat well and add pumpkin.
With a spoon, add dry ingredients and pecans. Fill jars half full.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
When done, remove one at a time from oven.
Put scalded lid on and seal.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Put rice in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add sausage, celery, peppers and onions.
Pour can of chicken broth over the top.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add enough milk for spreading consistency. Spread cream cheese on ham slices and roll around dill pickles. Chill. Before serving, cut in 1/2-inch slices.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
(Do not overbake.)

title: chili conqueso
directions: Saute chopped peppers, onions, tomatoes and chili pepper in oil until tender.
Add seasonings and cheese; cook slowly until cheese is melted and seasonings are blended.
Serve with corn chips.

title: top of stove pot roast
directions: Dredge roast with flour on all sides.
Heat a heavy pan or Dutch oven
over
moderate heat.
Brown roast slowly, using no fat.
When brown,
place
a rack under meat.
Add water and white vinegar.
Cover
and
simmer
over
very
low heat until tender. Half an
hour
before
serving,
add salt, pepper and mustard. Blend into juices, adding more liquid if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put in casserole.
Cook 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle other half can of noodles over top.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes more.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed (cool completely). Mix strawberries and strawberry glaze in separate bowl. In separate bowl, mix Philly cream cheese and confectioners sugar. After these are blended, fold in Cool Whip.
Pour Cool Whip mixture evenly over cake, then spread strawberry glaze mixture over Cool Whip mixture.

title: easy microwave "cheater" lasagne
directions: In a 2-quart pot, brown ground beef, separating meat with a fork as it cooks.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and salt.
Heat through.
Mix the egg in with the Ricotta cheese.

title: easy fettucine
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in skillet on low heat until golden brown.
Stir in process cheese spread, milk and Parmesan cheese until melted.
Add fettucine and mix lightly.
Serve immediately.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°
(325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan melt
butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour condensed
milk
over
crumbs evenly.
Top with nuts and M&M's. Press
down
firmly.
Bake
to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Chill and store at room temperature.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Combine all other ingredients and add broccoli.
Bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Layer items in bowl as listed.
Pour dressing over layered salad and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.
Serves approximately 10.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and butter for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats as soon as you turn the heat off. Stir and drop on waxed paper.

title: banana-apricot nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° or so for a glass pan).

title: salmon fried cakes
directions: Drain salmon liquid into measuring cup and add evaporated milk to measure 2/3 cup liquid.
Combine Bisquick mix, pepper, egg, liquid and lemon juice in mixing bowl.
Flake and stir in salmon. Stir in onion, green pepper, parsley, celery and dill weed and mix well.
Heat about 1-inch of oil in skillet to 365°.
Drop salmon mixture by teaspoon into hot oil and fry 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain and reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
In skillet, simmer onions in margarine.
Add flour and Pet milk to onions.
Cook until thick.
Add cheese chunks and all seasonings.
Cook on top of stove until cheese is melted.
Add drained spinach and mix well.
Put in 8 x 8 casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add vinegar, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over carrots, onion and pepper and let set for 2 hours or more.
This will keep for several days.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water.
Put in blender.
Add cream cheese; process to blend thoroughly.
Add apricot baby food; blend again. Add Cool Whip and blend.
Place in 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Refrigerate to set.

title: sally's chili
directions: Cover bottom of Dutch oven with olive oil and meat.
Add everything, but Masa Hirina.
Mix well and simmer 3 1/2 to 4 hours or until meat is tender.

title: the best rhubarb cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and bake for 10 to 15 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients well together. Pour over crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes or until set.

title: kathryn's famous tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in casserole until golden brown, about 1 hour, at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in pan.
Add a little sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together to form crumbs the rest of the ingredients.
Spread crumbs over top of apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: apricot chewies
directions: Beat
eggs
and
add sugar, butter
and
vanilla.
Coat apricots that have been cut in small pieces
and
small pieces of pecans in the flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch
pan that has been greased and
floured.
Bake
in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until
light
brown.
Cut in squares and coat in powdered sugar.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter at high speed of electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to cream cheese mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in almonds.

title: mushroom beef stew
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Season and boil until tender. add beef stew, corn, peas, potatoes and carrots.
Let cook for about 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Add onion soup mix, mushroom pieces and macaroni.
Let simmer until it has made a gravy.
Season to your taste.
Turn off.
Let cool.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Add sour cream and 2/3 container of Cool Whip (save 1/3 of Cool Whip for topping).
Layer wafers, bananas and mixture until all used up.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: stuffed chicken shells
directions: Cook shells.
Cook chicken breasts and cut into bite-size pieces.
Make stuffing and mix chicken into it; stuff shells with mixture.
Place in a 9 x 15-inch baking dish.
Mix the soups together and pour over shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Place zucchini in strainer and press out as much moisture as possible.
Mix with eggs and onion in small bowl.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into zucchini-egg mixture.
Heat oil on griddle or in skillet over medium heat.
Drop dough by tablespoon and brown lightly on both sides.
Serve immediately with butter and lemon wedges.

title: mommie's icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add egg and mix well. Sift flour before measuring. Sift all dry ingredients together and then add to sugar and egg mixture. Mix in vanilla. Fold in nuts. Turn dough out roughly two equal portions and roll up. Refrigerate dough overnight. Slice dough rolls into 1/4-inch slices and place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes. Makes 2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: silver dollar corn casserole
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together except grated cheese. Pour into 3 or 4 qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20-25 minutes.
Stir once after 10-15 minutes.
When all ingredients are done, remove from oven and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
May be cooked in microwave oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise, onion, margarine and cheese.
Add broccoli.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, covered.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
The last 10 minutes, put cracker crumbs on top and bake, uncovered.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Top with crackers.
Drizzle butter over all and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until onion and celery are tender.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in order given.
Stir in flour until mixture is stiff enough to hold spoon upright.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased, floured cookie pan.
Flatten.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Freeze 15 to 20 minutes.

title: orange icebox cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar well; add milk and heat.
Add beaten egg yolks after mixture is hot.
Cook until thick, then add gelatin which has been softened in orange juice and rind.
Let cool.
Beat egg whites; add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Fold into custard.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Heat sugar in skillet until sugar caramelizes.
Add peanuts. Pour onto buttered surface.
Stretch and pull candy into thin sheets.
Break up into individual pieces.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until slightly tender in salty water.
Drain. Cut broccoli into bite size pieces and place in a casserole dish. Mix eggs, onion, pepper, mayonnaise, soup and cheese together. Pour over broccoli.
Top with dressing.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Season chicken to taste (I use garlic powder, seasoned salt and lemon pepper).
Place in a baking dish. Add potatoes, carrots, bell pepper and onion.
Pour the Worcestershire sauce over the chicken.
Pour a packet of beef stew seasoning mix over the chicken and vegetables.
Pour the stewed tomatoes over the top.
Add mushrooms and cover with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: twice-cooked green beans
directions: Heat 1/2-inch water in 12-inch skillet to boiling and add green beans.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, until beans are tender-crisp.
Drain. Wipe skillet dry.
In same skillet, heat 2 tablespoons olive oil. Cook beans and 1/4 teaspoon crushed red pepper.
Stir frequently until beans are tender.
Remove from heat and stir in soy sauce.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and dice.
Fry bacon until crisp; lay on paper towel to cool.
Save bacon grease.
Add potatoes to bacon grease; salt and pepper.
Add vinegar to this.
Crumble and add bacon; add enough flour to make dressing to thicken.
Do this while in iron skillet and serve while hot.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Combine potatoes with cottage cheese, sour cream, garlic, salt and chives.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown ground turkey, onion and green pepper.
After browned, add garlic powder, chili powder, cumin, oregano, chiles, whole tomato and juice, tomato paste, chicken broth and salt.
Simmer in slow cooker 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Let bread dough raise.
Pinch dough in small pieces, about the size of a walnut, and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt oleo.
Mix together with milk, pudding, light brown sugar and cinnamon and pour over bread pieces.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer Tater Tots on bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake as directed on package.

title: cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine pineapple and marshmallows.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, eggs, flour and juice. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool and pour over pineapple mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ornaments
directions: Mix all ingredients; mix will be dry.
Roll out on cookie sheet or wax paper to desired thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter or knife into desired shapes.
Allow to dry 5 days.

title: curried rice and ham roll-ups
directions: Saute onion and butter until yellow.
Stir in rice, salt, pepper and curry powder.
Roll 1/2 cup curried rice mixture in each slice of boneless or boiled ham; secure with toothpick. Place in shallow baking dish and cover with foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: texas style cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet; cover and cook on medium heat for 10 minutes.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: I had two excellent reasons to begin
making gingerbread cookies, my children, Jamie and Jessica.
They are now 22 and 17 years old, but they still want gingerbread cookies at Christmastime!

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream
cheese and margarine;
add sugar and vanilla and blend well.

title: wesson oil cake
directions: Beat egg yolks with buttermilk, vanilla and Wesson oil.
Blend self-rising flour and soda.
Mix and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's ham glaze
directions: Mix well and pour over ham every 15 minutes.
Bake ham at 350° for 2 hours to heat through.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease square baking pan.
Flatten and cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in plastic Ziploc bag.
Place pieces of biscuits, several at a time, into bag and shake until coated.
Put into baking pan.
Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon, butter and water.
Pour over biscuits and toss lightly.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Place plate over pan and flip over.
Remove pan carefully.

title: mexi rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese together.
Heat in microwave 3 minutes on High.
Add cheese.
Serve.

title: duke's dilly potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes and cook in salted water until tender.
Place potatoes in a large bowl and add other ingredients.
Mix well. Sprinkle with extra dill and serve warm.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix the rhubarb, sugar and pineapple together well. Boil for 20 minutes over a medium high heat. Stir in jello powder. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix in large flat pan. Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Store in a tightly closed container.

title: polish dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour pineapple over this.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the fruit.
Cut margarine into slices and place over mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add ground meat and cook until done.
Drain well.
Combine beef mixture with tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce.
Cook on low for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Prepare noodles according to directions on box.
Use a large baking dish coated with Pam or margarine.
Start with sauce mix and pour 1 to 1 1/2 cups into dish.
Next, a layer of noodles. Then a layer of cheeses.
Continue to layer, making sure to finish with sauce being on top.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk  pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and half of the milk.
Add beaten eggs.
Add rest of the milk and stir in melted butter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat slightly and bake until knife comes out clean.
Yields 2 pies.

title: garbanzo bean soup
directions: Fry onion, garlic and green pepper in olive oil with chorizo sausage and ham until done but not brown.
Put all ingredients in beans and cook until done.
Very good!

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind all ingredients together; add sugar.
The relish is better made a day or two before eaten.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch (bite size) pieces.
In a medium bowl, mix the eggs, seasoned salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Dip steak pieces into the egg mixture, then coat with flour.
Fry in a large skillet. Drain on paper towel.
After all steak is fried, pour oil out of skillet and stir-fry diced pepper a couple of minutes.
Add French onion soup, 1 can water, tomato sauce and catsup.
Mix, then add steak and simmer 20 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add rinsed kidney beans and heat.
In a large bowl, cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
Add chips and cheese. Add meat with beans.
Pour dressing, to taste, over salad; mix well.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing as directed and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chicken; slice margarine over chicken evenly.
Cover with celery soup which has been mixed with bouillon.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Take out and scatter can of onions over evenly, then put back in and bake 10 more minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add cheese and green chilies.
Keep hot in crock-pot.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Combine melted oleo with egg and raisins. Mix remaining ingredients, add to liquid mixture a little at a time until blended. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: scones
directions: Sift first 4 items.
Cut in shortening until coarse.
Beat eggs together with buttermilk; then pour into dry ingredients and mix to make soft pouch.
Turn out dough on a lightly floured board and pat into 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut in 8 inch diameter with large cutter and each into 4 parts.
Total of 16.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil except cornstarch.
Add a little water to cornstarch so it dissolves.
Add cornstarch, little by little, stirring well.
Use non-aluminum pan with lid.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Dice cooked chicken.
Cook noodles, diced celery, green pepper, chopped onion, minced garlic and chopped parsley in chicken broth.
Combine chicken, noodles, vegetable mixture, mushroom soup, drained tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Add shredded cheese and bread crumbs.
Put in large casserole dish and top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned, about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare muffin mix by directions, including 2 additional teaspoons liquid to add moisture to mix.
Bake by directions.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble lightly.
Toss all vegetables and bacon; set aside.
Combine mayonnaise and pickle juice; mix well.

title: pizza salad
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients and pour over first 5.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Boil together sugar and Karo syrup and remove from heat.
Stir in the peanut butter until smooth.
Next, stir in corn flakes. Roll into balls and place on wax paper or serving dish.

title: tangy salad
directions: Heat to boiling the oil, sugar and vinegar; set aside to cool lightly.
Drain all vegetables and toss lightly.
Pour warm liquid over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
This salad keeps well for over a week.

title: mrs. pound's chocolate frosting
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, milk and cocoa until forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Let cool some, then beat until creamy enough to spread on cake.

title: pistachio surprise
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple (do not drain).
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit (liquid makes good jello with lemon, oranges or lime).
Put in Dutch oven.
Cover with mixture of butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve in place of vegetable.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: caramel lover's fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy saucepan, combine caramels, sweetened condensed milk and 1/2 cup shortening.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until melted and smooth.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, beat sugar and remaining 3/4 cup shortening until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
In small bowl, combine water, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add alternately with flour mixture, beating well.
Spread half the batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until center is set.
Spoon caramel mixture evenly over cake. Spread remaining batter evenly over caramel.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake for 40 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Loosen from sides of pan while warm.
Cool completely.

title: itch(serve like tabouleh)
directions: Soak bulgar in 1 1/2 cups hot tap water for approximately 2 hours before mixing with sauce; set aside.

title: hog pudding
directions: Cook sausage in pan until brown; drain.
Pour 1 can of corn in deep baking dish.
Spread sausage on top of corn.
Add second can of corn.
Place in hot oven and bake 20 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine and mix well dry ingredients in large saucepan.
Add water and stir to dissolve cornstarch.
Add 1 cup of berries and cook, stirring constantly, over moderate heat until thickened. Add lemon juice and stir well to mix; cool slightly.
Add 3 cups of berries.
Transfer all filling to pie shell.
Chill thoroughly. Serve with whipped cream, ice cream, etc.

title: day after christmas casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 bread cubes with eggs in large bowl.
Combine remaining cubes with milk; stir into egg mixture.
Add soup; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until well mixed. Pour into casserole; brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: milk chocolate bundt cake
directions: In a saucepan, heat the candy bar and chocolate syrup over low heat until melted; set aside to cool.

title: no-bake cheesecake pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt chips over medium-low heat; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in cream cheese until smooth. Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or until set.
Just before serving, sprinkle with toffee bits.
Serves:

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths and coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
In saucepan, melt butter, sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Place half of the biscuits in a greased Bundt pan; add pecans or raisins.
Pour half of the liquid over this.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownies.
Spread into well-greased pan.
Beat cheese, margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Pour evenly over brownie batter.
Bake 45 minutes or until top is brown.
Cool, frost and cut. Store in refrigerator, covered.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use glass or aluminum pan.
Place pats of butter on bottom of pan.
Place chicken on top of butter.
Pour salsa on top of chicken cutlets.
Sprinkle cheese on top of salsa. Bake for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat well with heavy-duty mixer. Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy (5 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine beef, beans, oregano, cumin and garlic powder.
Place 4 uncooked noodles in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread 1/2 of the beef mixture over the noodles.

Top with 4 more noodles and remaining beef mixture. Cover with remaining noodles. Combine water with picante sauce. Pour over all. Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until noodles are tender.
Combine sour cream, onions and olives. Spoon over casserole. Top with cheese. Bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted (about 5 minutes).

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain the fruit cocktail.
Add the marshmallows to the drained fruit.
Combine in top of a double boiler, over boiling water, the vinegar, egg or egg yolks and sugar.
Cook until mixture is thickened. Cool, then fold into fruit mixture. Whip, the cream and fold into mixture.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart saucepan and cook until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat and mix in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together in saucepan and pour over pan of Krispies Treats.

title: beef and cabbage
directions: Brown beef.
Mix onion, tomato sauce, juice, cloves and cinnamon. Put half of cabbage in 2-quart casserole; put half of meat mixture over cabbage.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramelized nuts
directions: Beat until stiff, egg white and cold water.
Mix together white sugar, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Toss pecans or peanuts in egg white.
Then pour into sugar mixture.
Spread out on cookie sheet.
Bake in 250° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: swiss sandwich puffs
directions: Combine mayonnaise,
onion and parsley; spread on small squares of	toasted
rye
bread.
Top
each
square with Swiss cheese. Broil 2 to 3 minutes.

title: hot beef din
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend sour cream and cream cheese in small bowl.
Add mayonnaise.
Stir in 3/4 c. pecans and beef. Transfer to oven proof dish; and top with remaining pecans.
Bake uncovered for 15 minutes serve with crackers.

title: cranberry shrub
directions: When ready to serve combine juices well; pour in punch bowl. Top with scoops of sherbet.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook
until
thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 small box strawberry jello, mix well and cool to room temperature. Slice
strawberries
in
a
baked and cooled pie crust. Spoon
on glaze,
be sure to cover well so berries won't turn dark.
Serve with
Cool
Whip.
Can also use a graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine black beans and 2 tablespoons salsa; mash with fork and stir until smooth.
On 12-inch serving plate, spread bean mixture into 10-inch circle.
Top with sour cream; spread to within 1/4-inch of edge of beans.
Top with one cup salsa, lettuce, cheese, olives, green onions and tomato.
Serve with Easy Tortilla Chips.
Makes 5 cups; 12 to 16 servings.

title: california coffee
directions: For each serving, pour 2 tablespoons brandy into mug.
Fill 2/3 full with hot strong coffee.
Top with 1 scoop (about 1/4 cup) chocolate ice cream.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter cupcake pan.
Sift together flours and baking powder; reserve.
Combine banana with brown sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs, milk and melted butter.
Stir in dry ingredients only until blended.
Quickly stir in chocolate chips.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon batter into cups.
Bake 25 minutes or until browned slightly.
Cool on rack.

title: "perfect pie crust"
directions: Mix salt and flour.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Add milk to mixture.
Divide.
Roll out half of mixture on floured surface to desired thickness to fit a 9-inch pan. Makes 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Cook sausage in medium saucepan over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain off all fat, except about 2 tablespoons.
Stir in flour, cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Gradually whisk in milk, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly, about 5 minutes.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add ginger ale, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Mix well.
Pour in Pyrex and refrigerate until jelled.

title: easy and quick lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Place in refrigerator overnight or until well set and serve.

title: vanilla cherry brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 9-inch square baking pan with foil. Grease and flour.
Blot cherries between layers of paper towels. In a small mixer bowl beat butter, sugar, eggs, corn syrup and Kirsch until blended.
Add flour, cocoa and baking powder.
Blend until combined.
Stir in chopped cherries, almonds and vanilla chips.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely. Cut into squares.
Garnish with Vanilla Chip Drizzle.

title: deluxe strawberry dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix and 2 tablespoons sugar. Cut in margarine.
Pat into round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Bake 10 minutes.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar, nutmeg, egg yolks and sour cream; spread over hot layer.
Bake 20 minutes; cool completely.
Prepare Strawberry Glace; cool slightly.
Arrange strawberries over layer and spread Strawberry Glace over the strawberries.
Makes 12 servings.

title: water chestnut appetizer
directions: Cut bacon strips into thirds.
Cut water chestnuts in half. Wrap each half chestnut in bacon strip and secure with toothpick. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix brown sugar and catsup and pour over chestnuts.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: jello cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water; add whole cranberry sauce to jello and water mixture.
Let gel until firm.
Add Cool Whip, then nuts. (This is good for a salad or dessert.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and flavoring well.
Add flour and mix well. Chill overnight.
Shape teaspoonfuls of dough in balls. Put on cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: uncooked peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk; boil one minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Blend all together.
Serve with cut up fruit.

title: ham (bologna) salad
directions: Cut the bologna into 1/8's.
Put into pan; add water.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Put in fridge until cold.
Put bologna through food grinder; also onion.
Mix bologna, onion and sweet pickle relish with mayo.
If it tastes sour, add package of sweetener.

title: mama's coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Add scalded milk and stir well. Cook over direct heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly. Beat egg yolks well. Stir in a little hot mixture and pour back into double boiler. Cook over boiling water 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

Beat egg whites until light and fluffy and gradually beat in the 6 tablespoons sugar until stiff. Fold 1/2 cup moist shredded coconut into the cooled filling, then fold about 1/2 of the meringue into the filling and pour into cooled pie shell. Spread remaining meringue so as to touch the edges of the crust all around. Place in a 425° oven for 4 1/2 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: I usually double recipe for 4 people.

title: peppermint patties
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk, extract and food coloring (if desired). Add conf. Sugar; beat on low speed until smooth and well blended. Turn mixture onto surface sprinkled with conf. Sugar. Knead lightly to form small ball. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on wax paper-lined baking sheets. Flatten each ball into a 1- 1/2 inch patty. Let dry 1 hour or longer; turn over and let dry at least 1 hour. With fork dip each patty into warm candy coating (drag fork lightly across rim of pan to remove excess coating) Invert onto wax paper-lined baking sheets; let stand until firm. Store covered at room temperature or in refrigerator.

title: sandy's spicy ears
directions: Boil water and cook Orechiette and bouillon cubes.
Meanwhile, put olive oil in saut pan with the chopped squash, peas and mint leaves.
Cook on medium heat.
While cooking, sprinkle on spices at will.

title: corned beef stew
directions: Cook until well blended.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box.
Add next 4 ingredients. Stir well.
Place in greased casserole and cook for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: amish cookies
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.

Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder, buttermilk, vanilla, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Drop 4 or 5 cookies on ungreased cookie sheet, each cookie measuring 1/4 cup. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake 7-8 minutes at 375°.

title: beef tips
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in covered dish for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over buttered noodles or rice.

title: spinach florentine
directions: Cook
spinach;	drain
and set aside, reserving liquid. Brown beef
and onion.
Drain grease.
Stir spinach liquid (1 cup)
and sauces into meat.
Simmer.	Cook noodles and drain. Combine cheese,
spinach,
bread crumbs, eggs, and 1/2 cup of oil.	Spread spinach-macaroni mixture in lightly greased dish with
the
meat mixture
on top.
Cook until bubbles at 350°. This casserole freezes well.

title: taco salad or dip
directions: Serve with taco chips, Tostitos or Doritos.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Slice cookie dough and cut into fourths. Place in greased mini muffin pans. Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. As soon as you take them out, place a peanut butter cup in the center.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; strain off any grease.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup bread crumbs mixed with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: honey cake
directions: Bring honey gently to boiling; then add the coffee.
Beat the eggs until light and lemon-colored; then add the oil a little at a time.
Beat until well blended; then add sugar.
Sift all dry ingredients; then add them to egg mixture with honey and coffee. Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan; bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Pour peas into bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle half of the cheese evenly over peas.
Arrange asparagus over the peas and cheese.
Add other half of the cheese, then the chopped eggs. Spoon mushroom soup over all and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat soup, Ro-Tel, sour cream and picante sauce in pan. Stir-fry chicken (diced) with desired seasonings.
Roll chicken, cheese, mushrooms, onions, green pepper and a little sauce in each tortilla.

title: harvest potatoes with herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

In a small bowl, combine seasonings. Place 2 tablespoons melted butter in a 10-inch nonstick skillet. Arrange 1/3 of the potato slices in a circular pattern in skillet. Sprinkle with about 1/4 teaspoon seasoning, 4 teaspoons melted butter and 2 tablespoons onion.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover tightly with foil.
Press layers down.
Bake 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Heat soup to boiling, add cream cheese, stirring until well blended.
Add gelatin mixture, mix well and let cool.
Add shrimp, mayonnaise, celery and onions. Pour into 6-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: frosted salad
directions: Mix and chill until firm.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheets. Mix together ingredients. Drop in powdered sugar. Place on cookie sheet. Heat oven to 350°. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Put roast and all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on high 6 to 8 hours. When meat is very tender, shred into pieces while still in crock-pot with juices. Serve on Italian beef rolls.
Make sure to put juice on meat when serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make 1-inch balls.
Flatten on cookie sheet (the thinner the better).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.
Yields 7 to 8 dozen. This is a really stiff batter, be patient.

title: crema de fruta(fruited jell-o)
directions: Boil gelatine with 1 cup water.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients in a Jell-O mold pan.
Pour the gelatine.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator for an hour or two.
Loosen on side.
When ready to serve, transfer into a platter.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Preheat electric oven to 350°.
Sift flour with sugar, soda and salt into a large bowl.
Mix in shortening; knead thoroughly (8 to 10 minutes).
Combine egg and almond extract; stir into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into balls, using 1 tablespoon of dough. Place on ungreased baking sheets; make a depression in the top with the thumb.
Press a blanched almond in the center.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Use leftover mashed potatoes and cooked cabbage.
Mix the potatoes and cabbage together.
Add salt and pepper to taste and chopped onion to taste.
Fry lightly in skillet until browned and hot.
Serve as vegetable and good to use up leftovers.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and warm in the microwave for 5 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; drain, peel and dice while hot.
Cook bacon in frying pan until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan.
Cook onion in bacon grease until golden brown.
Blend in flour, salt and sugar. Stir in the water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add vinegar and heat through. Pour the hot dressing over the hot potatoes.
Mix in the chopped bacon.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: eggs and sausage casserole(aka egg and sausage scramble)
directions: Grease or spray an 11 x 13-inch or 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings. Pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Ice with cream cheese icing.
Try not to eat the whole thing in 1 night.
It is even better eating the next day.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake into bite-size pieces.
