In a separate bowl, mix the Cool Whip, sour cream and evaporated milk together.
In a large bowl, put a layer of cake and 1/3 of Cool Whip mixture over cake. Make 2 layers (end with last of Cool Whip mixture).
Add glaze as last layer; top with strawberries.
Refrigerate overnight.
Do not mix.
Serve with long spoon.
Bon appetit!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for a few minutes until barely tender.
Drain well.
Saute chopped onion in small amount of oil or butter.
Add broccoli, soup, milk and cheese.
Turn into casserole dish and cover with stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: oatmeal cookies(oatsies)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In medium bowl, mix oats and brown sugar.
Stir together butter, syrup, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly into oat mixture.
Press dough evenly in bottom of pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool. Spread chocolate on top.
Spread nuts on chocolate.
Chill 1 hour. Cut into bars.
Yield:
32 cookies.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Spread on bread. Can be done 2-3 hours before serving. Put cucumbers on right before serving.

title: vegetable and chicken pot pie
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Add celery and stir over medium-high heat until crisp-tender. Stir in soup, milk, onion powder, thyme and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in vegetables and chicken; heat through. Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Arrange biscuits over hot filling.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown and filling is bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: filets de flet a la moutarde(broiled flounder fillets with mustard)
directions: *Other mild, white fish is good, too!

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground meat with onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients, except chips and grated cheese.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer crushed chips and meat mixture until gone.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: enchiritos
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Brown and drain.
Mix chili and enchilada sauce in pots and warm up.
Put small spoonful of meat mixture in a straight line across tortilla, then spoon chili mix on.
Add cheese and roll up.
Place some chili mix on bottom of oblong pan.
Finish rolling enchiritos and place in dish.
Use remaining chili mix to cover all.
Top with cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss-baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Halve potatoes lengthwise, then slice crosswise into 1/8-inch slices.
(Do not put potatoes in water after slicing.)
Immediately line up in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with slices overlapping, arranging in serving portions. Pour butter over potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper. Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese and then with Parmesan cheese.
Bake an additional 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: cheese danish
directions: Mix all together until creamy, except for rolls.
Put crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread to cover bottom. Spread mixture over rolls.
Put another package of rolls over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: gooey chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over chicken in baking dish. Bake at 250°-300° for 2-3 hours.
Continue to baste chicken until become sticky.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan. Add flour and salt.
Add chicken broth, slowly stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: normandy chocolate mousse
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan with waxed paper.
Arrange ladyfingers around sides and bottom of pan.
Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition. Blend in milk, vanilla and rum extract.
Blend in melted chocolate until well blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry; fold in chocolate mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into prepared pans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Beat peanut butter and margarine until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Mix in flour and salt. Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown. Immediately sprinkle baked dough with remaining chocolate chips. Let stand about 5 minutes until chips become shiny and soft. Spread the chocolate morsels with a knife as you would frosting. Cool completely and cut into bars.
Freezes well.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Saute meat until brown; drain. Add bell peppers and onion. Cook until done. Add tomatoes, water, salt and chili powder. Simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Add rice and kidney beans. Pour into baking dish. Cover and cook for 1 hour. Stir; bake a little longer or until rice is done. Bake at 350°.

title: chicken jacques
directions: In a covered skillet, saute chicken in a mixture of butter, oil and garlic, until tender, but not brown.
Remove to warm dish. Stir into skillet the peppers until they are limp.
Add the mushrooms and olives and cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove mixture to warm bowl.
Stir in 1 cup of sour cream, salt and pepper; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add sherry, chicken and reserved mushroom mixture and cook for 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: uncle eddie's favorite sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Chill thoroughly (at least 3 hours).
Roll on a well floured surface to 1/8 to 1/4 inch.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheet; remove to rack to finish cooling.
Decorate!

title: rhubarb jam
directions: When refrigeration is poor, put eggs in hot water (not boiling) for 15 seconds.
The eggs will keep from spoiling for 4 to 6 weeks without refrigeration.

title: coconut cream pie(no bake)
directions: Prepare whipped topping with 1 cup of milk as directed on package, using a large mixer bowl.
Add remaining milk and pie filling mix.
Blend and then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold in coconut.
Spoon into crust. Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry pizza pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump in cherries; sprinkle cake mix over cherries.
Cut butter into pats and place over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: talerina
directions: Chop then mix the following: brown bell pepper, onion, celery, garlic, ground chuck and sausage. Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, shoe peg corn, salt, and pepper. Combine both mixtures together.
Cook as spaghetti.
Add chopped black olives, 3/4 pound grated sharp cheese. Mix one package cooked wide noodles.
Bake 45 minutes in buttered casserole at 350°.
Top with 1/4 lb. sharp cheese.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: skillet corn and chicken
directions: Cook chicken in margarine in a skillet for 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove, set aside and drain off fat.
In skillet, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and broccoli is tender-crisp, stirring often.
Garnish with potato wedges.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and garlic (minced) until limp. Cook Italian sausage.
Warm pepperoni.
Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Reduce heat and simmer at least 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves.
Skim off fat before serving. Feeds 10.

title: bud's chicken casserole
directions: Place
rice
on
bottom
of oven dish.	Arrange chicken pieces on	top.
Sprinkle	onion
soup
mix over chicken. Pour soup mix over all. Cover and bake for 90 minutes at 350°.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer in a rectangular dish the sauerkraut, corned beef, shredded Swiss cheese, mixture of mayonnaise and Thousand Island dressing and rye bread.
Pour melted margarine over bread.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Remove from heat and add cornflakes and peanuts.
Press lightly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water, let cool.
Add 7-Up, marshmallows and pineapple.
Let set.
In a saucepan, beat egg; add butter, flour, pineapple juice and sugar.
Cook until thick; let cool and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on top of jello.
Grate frozen cream cheese on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: butter rum sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; add brown sugar and Borden whipping cream.
Boil rapidly 8 to 10 minutes; add rum.
Pour over bread pudding.
Serve warm.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: tacos
directions: Saute beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until beef is no longer red.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings. Simmer for 20 minutes or until somewhat thickened, stirring often. Warm taco shells in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Spoon beef mixture into shells.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.

title: lo-cal dip
directions: Blend until creamy.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: mom's easy fried chicken
directions: Mix eggs and milk in bowl.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and herbs on plate.
Dip chicken in milk and then roll in flour mixture.
Place in pan with Crisco and fry until brown.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Cut off top of bread and hollow out, forming crust shell. Tear bread into small pieces to make 2 cups.
Brown beef in oil; mix in remaining ingredients except cheese slices and bread pieces.
Simmer 4 to 5 minutes and stir in bread pieces.
Fill crust with mixture.
Cut cheese slices in half diagonally and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese melts.
Replace top and serve.
Yield:
4 to 8 servings.

title: yum-a-selta(hearty dish)
directions: Brown meat with salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Add tomato soup.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Layer meat mixture (1/2), noodle mixture (1/2), cheese (1/2) and repeat process.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: batty cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients, add egg and buttermilk.
Stir till smooth.
Drop by tablespoons on greased griddle.
This is a kind of corn meal pancake.
Crispy around the edges and very tasty with butter and syrup.

title: date and nut cookies
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add in sugar and vanilla extract and mix well.
Add in flour, baking powder and salt and mix well. Stir in dates and walnuts.
Pour into greased square pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool cut into squares and dip in 10x sugar.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Cream shortening and vanilla.
Add sugar; cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs and pumpkin; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Stir into pumpkin mixture, mixing until smooth.
Blend in coconut and nuts.
Spread batter in pan; bake for about 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: hungarian paprikas
directions: In large pan, heat oil.
Add meat cubes and cook over medium heat until well browned.
Remove meat to bowl.
Saute onions in drippings until tender and golden brown.
Return meat to pan. Add paprika, salt, pepper, garlic salt and caraway seed, stirring until well blended with meat.
Stir in 3/4 can of beef broth. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until the meat is fork-tender.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add syrup and water. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is thick and clear.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O; stir until completely dissolved.
If a darker color is desired add red food coloring.
Cool sauce and add berries.
Pour in pie shell and refrigerate 2 hours or more.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6 or 8.
I save a few big berries to put on top of whipped cream.

title: coconut topping
directions: Melt butter in a small glass bowl in microwave (1 minute). Add remaining ingredients to butter and mix well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with a fork and bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender. Cool slightly. Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell. Set shells aside. Put pulp into a small mixing bowl; add cream cheese, chives, salt and pepper. Beat until smooth.

Add milk, a tablespoon at a time, beating until fluffy. Put mixture back into the shells and sprinkle with paprika. Place in a baking dish and cover loosely with foil. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; uncover and bake 10 more minutes or until heated.

title: chocolatetown pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell and set aside.
In bowl, cream butter; add eggs and vanilla. Combine sugar and flour; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool about one hour; serve warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 3 items together.
Blend well the rest of the ingredients together.
Pour in 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Stew chicken in large Dutch oven-sized pot. Use a large amount of water. Stew until
tender. Remove chicken. Add sliced carrots, diced potatoes, celery, green beans, broccoli and onion. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar.
Press down with glass or fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cookies will be soft. Cool on sheets until set, about 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: french toast
directions: Break eggs in bowl; add milk, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat.
Dip sliced loaf bread in mixture on both sides.
Fry in pan with butter until golden brown.	Add butter on top with syrup.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Bring water to boil.
Cook cabbage about 7 minutes or until just wilted.
Drain cabbage.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Grease a baking dish with margarine or butter.
Put half of cabbage in bottom of dish.
Cover with half of the soup.
Layer half of cheese over soup.
Repeat layers in same order using remaining cabbage, soup and cheese.
Sprinkle crushed cracker or bread crumbs on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Uncover.
Cook 5 minutes longer for crackers to crisp.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easiest-ever cocoa fudge
directions: Microwave sugar, cocoa, milk and butter on High (full power) until butter is melted, about 2 to 3 minutes; stir until smooth. Blend in vanilla
and nuts.
Spread into buttered 8-inch square pan; cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: Mix all together and simmer
about
hour or until it cooks down thick enough to use
on
hot dogs.
Stir often when it first starts cooking.

title: butter fingers(christmas cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add vanilla; grind the nuts and add to this.
Add the cold water, then the flour and salt.
Knead thoroughly.
Roll small amount at a time by hand in a roll the size of your finger, cut in pieces about an inch long.
Cook in preheated oven at 300°.
Cook until light brown, about half an hour, depending on your oven.
When cool, dust cookies with powdered sugar.
Make only one batch at a time.
When cool, store in a tight can lined with wax paper.
These keep a long time and the flavor improves with age.
Yields 24.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add milk, sugar, chocolate morsels and vanilla flavor.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Check with cool water; if forms into a ball, add nuts.
If ball does not form, cook 5 minutes longer.
Spread in a buttered pan.

title: cranberry sauce and glaze(for chicken, duck, cornish hen)
directions: Mix together cranberry sauce, orange juice, duck sauce and wine.
Use half mixture to baste poultry and bake.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift dry ingredients 5 times.
Add milk and shortening and beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flavoring and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: the elvis delite
directions: Toast two (2) slices of whole wheat bread.
Apply one thick coating of smooth peanut butter.
Slice one large banana onto applied peanut butter and toast.
Cover with plain slice of toast. Cut diagonally from upper right to lower left.
Then enjoy a very tasty Elvis delite.

title: scented christmas ornaments
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in applesauce; mix well.
Stir in glue; mix well.

title: pecan crunch chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and put into oven to melt.
Combine buttermilk and egg. Combine flour, pecans, paprika, salt, pepper and sesame seed.
Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk mixture, then place in plastic bag with flour mixture.
Shake well to coat chicken lightly.
Place skin-side down in baking dish; turn pieces to coat with butter. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender and golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: double chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, butter, milk and vanilla in medium bowl.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oats, peanut butter chips and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately take from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.
(Self-rising flour can be used.)

title: carrots a la orange
directions: Wash carrots, scrub with stiff brush and cut in half.
Cook until just tender. Melt butter or margarine in heavy skillet. Add sugar and orange juice.
Let bubble 2 to 3 minutes. Add carrots, tossing now and then to glaze well over medium heat.
Top with orange slices and sprinkle with nutmeg, turning now and then so carrots and oranges are thoroughly glazed.
Serve at once!
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; take off bones and put in casserole dish.
Mix milk with chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with chicken broth and pour on top of milk mixture and heat in 350° oven.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients, then fold in remainder, ending with Cool Whip. Chill.

title: pineapple - lime ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and juice. Gradually add gelatin to cream cheese, mixing until blended. Chill until thickened, but not set.
Fold in marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Garnish with flaked coconut and marshmallows.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat well.
Add vanilla, potato chips and
beat
together.
Add nuts and mix well (do not beat now). Drop
by
teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Then put mixer away and stir in flour.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients, mixing well.
Fold in chocolate pieces and nuts. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Let cool on wire rack.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in half. Discard tips.
Place wings in pan large enough so wings do not overlap each other.
Sprinkle pepper and salt.
Mix next 6 ingredients. Add hot water and blend well.
Pour this over wings. Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours. Remove foil.
Lower heat to 300° and baste wings often for about 30 minutes.
Drain wings on paper towels. Serve hot or cold.

title: moist creamy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Then poke holes down through cake with utility fork.
Meanwhile, combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup of coconut in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Spoon over warm cake, allowing liquid to soak down through holes.
Cool completely.
Fold 1/2 cup of the coconut into whipped topping and spread over cake. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill overnight.
Store leftover cake in refrigerator.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
In bacon grease, fry potatoes, onion and green pepper until tender.
Dice bacon and add.
Add salt and pepper.

title: chicken with dried beef
directions: Line the bottom of a baking dish with half of chipped beef. Wrap each piece of chicken with a strip of bacon and place on top of beef.
Place remaining beef on top of chicken.
Blend soup and sour cream until smooth and pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: cinnamon rice and lentils
directions: Combine the raisins with the apple juice.
Set aside to plump. Place the broth and cinnamon stick in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir in the lentils, rice, oil and raisins with the apple juice and return to a boil.
Reduce the heat to low and cover tightly.
Let the rice simmer, undisturbed, for about 45 minutes. Uncover the pan and toss the rice mix with the remaining ingredients.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Garnish with a dollop of plain yogurt and pecans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all, reserving 3/4 cup of pecans.
Chill.
Roll into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Garnish by rolling in the remaining pecans, mixed with dried or fresh parsley, if desired.
May garnish with pieces of maraschino cherries for color.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Combine with pumpkin.
Add sugar, oil and water.
Add flour and mix well.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool the peas.
Break lettuce into large bowl. Fry bacon crisp and break it up.
Chop onion and green pepper.

title: cheese salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water.
Add other ingredients to gelatin mixture.
Pour in 9 x 2-inch pan (glass or metal).
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares.
Serve with dressing of 1/2 cup Miracle Whip and 1/2 cup whipped cream.
Delicious.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and bake uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grammy's cinnamon cucumber rings or mock apple rings
directions: Day One:
Combine 2 gallons water and pickling lime.
Add cucumber rings, peeled and sliced about 3/8-inch thick.
Scoop out the seeds.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: apple cheese torte
directions: In medium bowl, using pastry blender or fork, combine cookie crumbs and margarine.
Press on bottom and up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan or use pie pan.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: For Sauce:
Stir together the soup, milk and pepper in a medium mixing bowl.
Set aside.

title: pork chops vera cruz with rice
directions: Brown pork chops in oil in 10-inch skillet, turning to brown well on both sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Sprinkle with flour, brown sugar, mustard, salt and garlic.
Add onion and wine.
Cover and cook over low heat until chops are tender, about 1 hour.
Add water as needed and spoon sauce over chops several times. Meanwhile, cook rice according to package.
Add green pepper to pork 15 minutes before end of cooking time.
Top with pimiento. Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: scallops and linguine in alfredo sauce
directions: Fry scallops in butter and garlic in frying pan until scallops are cooked.
Cook broccoli for 20 minutes and drain. Cook noodles for 20 minutes; drain and let cool.
Heat white sauce.
Mix noodles, broccoli and sauce with scallops and serve.

title: vincent's marinade
directions: Very good for steaks, etc.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels with butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese with Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar.
Spread over pretzel crust.
In a large bowl, mix jello, water, strawberries and pineapple.
Chill mixture until partially set.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Let chill a few hours before serving.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box recipe.
Bake in 16 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is baking, mix 1 cup evaporated milk and 1 cup sugar; bring to rapid boil and then remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add coconut and almonds and mix well.
Spread mixture over hot cake.
In saucepan add 1/2 cup margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Bring to a rapid boil; remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate bits; stir until melted.
Spread over coconut layer.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Pour into buttered pan and bake at 300° until brown.
While still hot, cover with icing.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add crumbled cornbread and mix well.
Add a few pinches of crushed sage and 1/2 to 3/4 t. of poultry seasoning if desired.
Bake at 300 degrees for 35 - 45 min. or until set.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl to make a stiff dough, using a little more flour if needed.
Roll very thin on floured surface; let stand 20 minutes.
Slice 1/4-inch thick wide.
Drop into boiling soup or broth.
Cook, uncovered, approximately 10 minutes. Makes 3 cups cooked noodles.

title: chinese hot dish
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients.
Mix and place the remaining ingredients in a casserole dish. Add the hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Salt hamburger only slightly as soy sauce is salty. Put Chinese noodles on top of casserole for the last 15 minutes.

title: wee lemon cakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions except omit 3 tablespoons water.
Drop by teaspoon into greased and floured miniature cupcake pans.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Remove cakes when cooked and immediately drop cakes into mixture.
When coated, remove from mixture with slotted spoon and place on wax paper.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cheese-crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover mixture and refrigerate.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yields 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: grandma warmann's whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir until dissolved fully.
Let stand.
Pour 3 cups boiling water over 1 1/2 cups cracked wheat.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add to cracked wheat, the bran, 1 1/2 cups warm water, salt, brown sugar, oil, whole wheat flour and 2 cups white flour.
Mix well and add dissolved yeast. Beat hard and add more white flour to make firm dough (5 to 6 cups).
Knead on floured surface 5 to 6 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and put into greased bread pans.
Let rise again.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 full loaves.

title: microwave choco oats drops
directions: Place sugar, milk and butter in a quart glass casserole dish. Microwave 3 to 5 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place in preheated 350° oven. Bake for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Butter and flour an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and butter to form a dough.
Press the dough evenly into the prepared pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Allow this to cool; prepare remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Whisk together remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour the mixture over cooled shell and bake 25 minutes. Allow to cool, then sprinkle with confectioners sugar and almonds. Cut into bars and serve.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix Cheez Whiz, cream of chicken soup and chunk chicken together; set aside.
Steam broccoli and margarine (with onion if you like) until done.
Place on top of rice mixture, then add cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: asparagus with mustard sauce(microwave)
directions: Trim off tough ends of asparagus.
In microwave dish, arrange asparagus alternately, tips and ends.
Add water.
Cover with plastic.
Vent 1 corner.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes, or until tender-crisp.
Rearrange halfway through.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, buttermilk and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight before baking.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Keeps 6 weeks.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Wrap each breast with bacon and secure with toothpick.
Cover bottom of flat greased baking dish with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken on beef.
Mix soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour on top. Bake at 275° uncovered for 3 hours.
Serve with rice.
Serves 8.

title: play dough(stovetop recipe)
directions: Mix in a medium pot, flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Combine and add water, food coloring and oil.
Cook over medium heat and stir (about 3 to 5 minutes).
It will look like a globby mess and you'll think it's not turning out, but it will.
When it forms a ball in the center of the pan, turn out and knead on a lightly floured surface.
Store in an airtight container or plastic bag.

title: swedish rye bread(bread machine recipe)
directions: Mix dry ingredients, except yeast and set aside.
Pour water and molasses into bread machine.
Add dry ingredients, yeast and butter.
Set machine for dough cycle. During the knead cycle, add any additional water or flour to bring dough to a soft (not gummy) consistency.
At end of dough cycle, turn onto floured surface. Let rest for 15 minutes.
Form into a round loaf.
Place onto a lightly greased baking sheet that has been sprinkled with corn meal.
Cover with a clean dish towel and let rise until doubled. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Loaf should make a hollow sound when tapped on the bottom.
Cool for 15 minutes before slicing.
Serve buttered with paper-thin sliced ham for a special treat.

title: chocolate nut zucchini cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Let cool.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or Bundt cake pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, beat eggs until thick and light. Gradually add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add salad oil and cooled chocolate; beat until well blended.
At low speed add dry ingredients, mixing until smooth. Add zucchini and nuts with wooden spoon.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until surface springs back when pressed lightly.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Or may bake in 3 loaf pans for 1 hour.

title: chocolate mint pudding
directions: Combine first 3 items in a medium saucepan.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until smooth.
Cook over medium-low heat for 25 to 30 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat; stir in liqueur and vanilla.
Spoon mixture into individual dessert dishes.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, sprinkle evenly with crushed peppermint.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put into refrigerator to cool. After cooling, shape into ball and sprinkle with even amounts of paprika and chili powder.

title: strawberry and pineapple dip
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature; mix in sugar and vanilla. Serve with strawberries or pineapple of piccolo cookies (Nabisco).

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine rest of ingredients.
Add dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix in order the first 8 ingredients.
Mix cocoa and hot water.
Add to batter; pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Mix brown sugar and cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix chicken soup, peppers, cheese and onion.
Layer in casserole, starting with cheese mixture, meat and chips.
Make edge with chips.
Makes 3 layers of cheese, 2 of meat and chips.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal mix, eggs, oil, milk, corn, sugar, garlic and onion and mix well.
Mix in peppers and cheese.
Pour into well-greased 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until brown and firm.
Wonderful with beans!

title: vegetable chili
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Add all ingredients into crock-pot; simmer until done.
Feeds a large family.
Great with grandma's cornbread.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak stale bread in milk.
Crush with hands until well mixed. Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and fruit.
Pour margarine in bottom of thick pan and bake until very firm.
Let cool and serve in cubes with lemon sauce.

title: jane evans' sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat on medium in skillet.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients in a bowl.
Pour over browned meat and simmer 45 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch, blended with enough cold water to make smooth.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: italian easter bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
In separate large bowl, add milk, butter, sugar, salt, egg yolks, citron, orange and lemon peel and raisins.
Mix in 1 cup flour.
Add softened yeast.
Beat in remaining flour.
Toss on floured board and knead until smooth. Shape into ball and place in oiled bowl.
Brush top with oil and let rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Take 2/3 of dough and divide into 4 pieces.
Shape each into long roll (18 x 1-inch).
Twist 2 rolls into circle or nest and place on greased sheet.
Place colored eggs in dough.
Do other roll.
Also roll 6 thin pieces from remaining dough and crisscross over eggs.
Brush top with butter and let rise again 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. When cooled, drizzle top with 1 cup confectioners sugar and 1 tablespoon milk.
Makes 2 rings.

title: hamburg noodle bake
directions: Fry hamburg, salt, pepper and onion until brown.
Add tomato sauce; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook noodles in salt water.
Put 1/2 of the noodles in greased casserole.
Spread on top 1/3 of the sour cream, then 1/3 of the meat mixture.
Repeat until all is used up.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: "a happy home"
directions: Take 1 large field, half a dozen children, 2 or 3 small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.
Mix the children and dogs well together; put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles; sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: port wine congealed salad
directions: *Can use Welches grape juice instead of wine.

title: oven easy beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Beat together the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy, 1 to 2 minutes.
Beat in cocoa.
Add flour; beat until well blended.
Stir in pecans by hand.
Spread evenly in a wax paper lined, 8-inch square glass dish.
Cook in microwave oven on High for 3 minutes.
Turn dish a quarter turn; continue to cook on High 2 1/2 to 3 minutes longer.
Let cool.
Sift powdered sugar over top, if desired.
Cut into 16 to 24 squares.

title: rice-pot jambalaya
directions: Spray rice pot with Pam.
Add melted oleo.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion, raw rice, bell pepper, chicken broth and protein of choice.
Stir.
Cook until rice is done.

title: chicken divan(great for company)
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix together mayonnaise, soup and curry powder.
Layer broccoli, chicken and the mayonnaise, soup and curry powder mixture.
Sprinkle on cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: freezer peach preserves
directions: Peel and pit peaches.
Grind or finely chop fruit.
Measure 2 1/4 cups into large bowl.
Add lemon juice and sugar; let set 20 minutes.
Mix 3/4 cup water and Sure-Jell in small saucepan. Bring to a full boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
At once, stir into fruit.
Continue stirring 3 minutes.
Immediately ladle into containers.
Cover with lids and let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Store in freezer or small amounts may be kept in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Cook longer than ordinary pancakes.
Edges should be crisp.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: In a nonaluminum pan, simmer ingredients for 15 to 20 minutes. Strain.
This is good hot or cold.

title: creton
directions: Cook pork and onion over low heat, stirring frequently to prevent sticking.
Add salt and pepper; continue cooking for about 2 hours.
Add ground cloves the last 15 minutes.
For smooth texture, mash with potato masher.
To lessen grease, ladle off after removing from heat.
Also, when it sets up after cooling, scrape off fat with a knife or spoon.

title: black midnight cakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch or two 9-inch or 8-inch pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly. Beat 3 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake in oblong pan about 45 minutes, round pan 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Mix Bisquick, salt, pepper, marjoram, parsley, oil and cheeses until well blended.
Fold in chopped onion and sliced zucchini.
Pour into pie plate. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: In 12-inch skillet over
medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken, a few
pieces
at
a time, until browned on all sides; remove chicken to roasting pan as it browns.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Place broccoli on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Cover with stuffing.
Pour prepared soup over stuffing and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Nice dish for covered dish dinners.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into thin slices to measure about 4 cups. Heat 3 T margarine in saucepan, until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly; remove from heat. Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: no cal, no fat, no sodium cake
directions: Combine ingredients and serve.
Great for all diets.

title: meatballs
directions: Put meatballs in slow cooker/Crock Pot.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Heat on low until thoroughly heated through about 4 hours.
Stir a few times during the cooking process to incorporate sauces.

title: reba's graham candy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and crumbs.
Stir well.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch pan or 2 plates.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates and water; cool.
Add sugar and egg; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Grease hands; shape into balls. Roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sweet pie dough
directions: Beat eggs very well.
Add to mixture of flour, baking powder, sugar, Crisco and vanilla.
Chill overnight.
Roll on floured board for desired size.

title: first prize chocolate fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Butter 9-inch spring-form pan. Wrap outside of pan securely with foil. Heat chocolate with water and coffee powder in saucepan over very low heat, stirring occasionally, just until chocolate is melted. Cool to room temperature. Beat butter in mixer bowl until creamy. Beat in sugar until light and fluffy, 5 minutes. Beat in egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each. At low speed, gradually beat in flour. Stir in cooled chocolate mixture. In clean bowl, beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually increase speed and beat until stiff but not dry. Fold into chocolate mixture. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 60 to 65 minutes, until toothpick inserted in cake about 1-inch from side comes out clean. (Top may crack.) Cool in pan on rack. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove side of pan. Sift confectioners sugar lightly over top of cake. Makes 14 to 16 servings.

title: garden pasta
directions: Saute all ingredients together; stir often.
When veggies are tender and tomatoes dissolve, pour mixture over pasta in a Pyrex dish.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and enjoy!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together, then freeze.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer 10 minutes prior to serving time.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Sift flour and powdered sugar together. Set aside. In a large bowl, beat egg whites (at room temperature), cream of tartar and salt until foamy. Add second amount of sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time. Beat on high until meringue holds stiff peaks. Gently fold in flavorings. Sprinkle flour-sugar mixture 1/4 cup at a time over meringue, folding in gently just until flour mixture disappears. Push batter into ungreased Bundt pan and gently cut through batter. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until top springs back when touched with finger. Turn on wire rack until completely cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package; drain well. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from stove and stir.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Mix well.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.
Let cool.

title: chinese spring rolls
directions: Cut meat into small thin pieces.

(Tofu may be substituted). In large frying pan or wok, heat 2 tablespoons of oil until smoking. Stir-fry meat, small portion at a time, and set aside. Add more oil if necessary, and stir-fry vegetables until crisp-tender.

title: greek crackers
directions: Mix ingredients; pour over crackers.
Stir until absorbed. Store in airtight container.

title: hot cinnamon fruit
directions: Drain fruit very well and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Dot with butter.
Mix brown sugar and spices and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Decorate with cherries.

title: creole beans
directions: Bring water to boil and add beans.
Boil 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Return to heat and simmer, covered, until tender, a fork pierces a single bean easily; drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in a little oil.
Stir in flour, seasonings and sugar.
Add tomatoes and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in cooked beans; heat through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Microwave chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in a large microwaveable bowl on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and the remaining milk until well blended.
Refrigerate to cool, about 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Break up hash browns and squeeze water out.
Melt butter.
Mix everything together and put in a buttered dish.
Mix corn flake crumbs and 1/8 cup of butter and sprinkle on top before you bake. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brown beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 inch cubes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roll in flour and brown in the fat.
Add water, cover and simmer until almost tender, 2 to 3 hours.
Add vegetables, season with salt and pepper and continue to simmer until vegetables are done, stirring occasionally.

title: crab melt-a-ways
directions: Melt the oleo and cheese; add the other ingredients and mix. Split the muffins and cut into fourths.
Spread mix on muffins and broil for 5 minutes.

title: hummingbird muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients; add oil, eggs and stir but don't beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon into 3 (9-inch) cake pans that are greased and floured or bake in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all other ingredients with ground beef.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Delicious!

title: o' henry bars
directions: Bring to a boil syrup and white sugar and remove from heat. Mix in peanut butter.
Add Special K cereal.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butterscotch chips and spread on top, then melt chocolate chips and spread over.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and debone hen.
Put peppers, celery and onions in broth and simmer.
Partially cook spaghetti in water and pour in sieve. Rinse with cold water to remove excess starch.
Add to broth and simmer until tender; add diced chicken, mushrooms, pimento and ripe olives.
Mix in the grated cheese.
Serve hot with green salad and crisp crackers.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
In ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, mix cereal, nuts, croutons and pretzel sticks.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix well.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer pork chops, potatoes and soup.
Cover and bake at 420° for 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking until brown.
